51const char* StreamTypeToString(
52 webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType type) {
53 switch (type) {
54 case webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kMedia:
55 return "kMedia";
56 case webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kRtx:
57 return "kRtx";
58 case webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kFlexfec:
59 return "kFlexfec";
60 }
61 return nullptr;
62}

64bool IsEnabled(const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials,
65 absl::string_view name) {
66 return absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup(name), "Enabled");
67}
68
69bool IsDisabled(const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials,
70 absl::string_view name) {
71 return absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup(name), "Disabled");
72}
73
74bool PowerOfTwo(int value) {
75 return (value > 0) && ((value & (value - 1)) == 0);
76}
77
78bool IsScaleFactorsPowerOfTwo(const webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig& config) {
79 for (const auto& layer : config.simulcast_layers) {
80 double scale = std::max(layer.scale_resolution_down_by, 1.0);
81 if (std::round(scale) != scale || !PowerOfTwo(scale)) {
82 return false;
83 }
84 }
85 return true;
86}

88void AddDefaultFeedbackParams(VideoCodec* codec,
89 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
90 // Don't add any feedback params for RED and ULPFEC.
91 if (codec->name == kRedCodecName || codec->name == kUlpfecCodecName)
92 return;
93 codec->AddFeedbackParam(FeedbackParam(kRtcpFbParamRemb, kParamValueEmpty));
94 codec->AddFeedbackParam(
95 FeedbackParam(kRtcpFbParamTransportCc, kParamValueEmpty));
96 // Don't add any more feedback params for FLEXFEC.
97 if (codec->name == kFlexfecCodecName)
98 return;
99 codec->AddFeedbackParam(FeedbackParam(kRtcpFbParamCcm, kRtcpFbCcmParamFir));
100 codec->AddFeedbackParam(FeedbackParam(kRtcpFbParamNack, kParamValueEmpty));
101 codec->AddFeedbackParam(FeedbackParam(kRtcpFbParamNack, kRtcpFbNackParamPli));
102 if (codec->name == kVp8CodecName &&
103 IsEnabled(trials, "WebRTC-RtcpLossNotification")) {
104 codec->AddFeedbackParam(FeedbackParam(kRtcpFbParamLntf, kParamValueEmpty));
105 }
106}

108// This function will assign dynamic payload types (in the range [96, 127]) to
109// the input codecs, and also add ULPFEC, RED, FlexFEC, and associated RTX
110// codecs for recognized codecs (VP8, VP9, H264, and RED). It will also add
111// default feedback params to the codecs.
112// is_decoder_factory is needed to keep track of the implict assumption that any
113// H264 decoder also supports constrained base line profile.
114// Also, is_decoder_factory is used to decide whether FlexFEC video format
115// should be advertised as supported.
116// TODO(kron): Perhaps it is better to move the implicit knowledge to the place
117// where codecs are negotiated.
118template <class T>
119std::vector<VideoCodec> GetPayloadTypesAndDefaultCodecs(
120 const T* factory,
121 bool is_decoder_factory,
122 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
123 if (!factory) {
124 return {};
125 }
126
127 std::vector<webrtc::SdpVideoFormat> supported_formats =
128 factory->GetSupportedFormats();
129 if (is_decoder_factory) {
130 AddH264ConstrainedBaselineProfileToSupportedFormats(&supported_formats);
131 }
132
133 if (supported_formats.empty())
134 return std::vector<VideoCodec>();
135
136 // Due to interoperability issues with old Chrome/WebRTC versions only use
137 // the lower range for new codecs.
138 static const int kFirstDynamicPayloadTypeLowerRange = 35;
139 static const int kLastDynamicPayloadTypeLowerRange = 65;
140
141 static const int kFirstDynamicPayloadTypeUpperRange = 96;
142 static const int kLastDynamicPayloadTypeUpperRange = 127;
143 int payload_type_upper = kFirstDynamicPayloadTypeUpperRange;
144 int payload_type_lower = kFirstDynamicPayloadTypeLowerRange;
145
146 supported_formats.push_back(webrtc::SdpVideoFormat(kRedCodecName));
147 supported_formats.push_back(webrtc::SdpVideoFormat(kUlpfecCodecName));
148
149 // flexfec-03 is supported as
150 // - receive codec unless WebRTC-FlexFEC-03-Advertised is disabled
151 // - send codec if WebRTC-FlexFEC-03-Advertised is enabled
152 if ((is_decoder_factory &&
153 !IsDisabled(trials, "WebRTC-FlexFEC-03-Advertised")) ||
154 (!is_decoder_factory &&
155 IsEnabled(trials, "WebRTC-FlexFEC-03-Advertised"))) {
156 webrtc::SdpVideoFormat flexfec_format(kFlexfecCodecName);
157 // This value is currently arbitrarily set to 10 seconds. (The unit
158 // is microseconds.) This parameter MUST be present in the SDP, but
159 // we never use the actual value anywhere in our code however.
160 // TODO(brandtr): Consider honouring this value in the sender and receiver.
161 flexfec_format.parameters = {{kFlexfecFmtpRepairWindow, "10000000"}};
162 supported_formats.push_back(flexfec_format);
163 }
164
165 std::vector<VideoCodec> output_codecs;
166 for (const webrtc::SdpVideoFormat& format : supported_formats) {
167 VideoCodec codec(format);
168 bool isCodecValidForLowerRange =
169 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, kFlexfecCodecName) ||
170 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, kAv1CodecName);
171 if (!isCodecValidForLowerRange) {
172 codec.id = payload_type_upper++;
173 } else {
174 codec.id = payload_type_lower++;
175 }
176 AddDefaultFeedbackParams(&codec, trials);
177 output_codecs.push_back(codec);
178
179 if (payload_type_upper > kLastDynamicPayloadTypeUpperRange) {
180 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
181 << "Out of dynamic payload types [96,127], skipping the rest.";
182 // TODO(https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=12194):
183 // continue in lower range.
184 break;
185 }
186 if (payload_type_lower > kLastDynamicPayloadTypeLowerRange) {
187 // TODO(https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=12248):
188 // return an error.
189 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
190 << "Out of dynamic payload types [35,65], skipping the rest.";
191 break;
192 }
193
194 // Add associated RTX codec for non-FEC codecs.
195 if (!absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, kUlpfecCodecName) &&
196 !absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, kFlexfecCodecName)) {
197 if (!isCodecValidForLowerRange) {
198 output_codecs.push_back(
199 VideoCodec::CreateRtxCodec(payload_type_upper++, codec.id));
200 } else {
201 output_codecs.push_back(
202 VideoCodec::CreateRtxCodec(payload_type_lower++, codec.id));
203 }
204
205 if (payload_type_upper > kLastDynamicPayloadTypeUpperRange) {
206 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
207 << "Out of dynamic payload types [96,127], skipping rtx.";
208 // TODO(https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=12194):
209 // continue in lower range.
210 break;
211 }
212 if (payload_type_lower > kLastDynamicPayloadTypeLowerRange) {
213 // TODO(https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=12248):
214 // return an error.
215 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
216 << "Out of dynamic payload types [35,65], skipping rtx.";
217 break;
218 }
219 }
220 }
221 return output_codecs;
222}

226 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec_name, kVp9CodecName);

229static std::string CodecVectorToString(const std::vector<VideoCodec>& codecs) {
230 rtc::StringBuilder out;
231 out << "{";
232 for (size_t i = 0; i < codecs.size(); ++i) {
233 out << codecs[i].ToString();
234 if (i != codecs.size() - 1) {
235 out << ", ";
236 }
237 }
238 out << "}";
239 return out.Release();
240}
241
242static bool ValidateCodecFormats(const std::vector<VideoCodec>& codecs) {
243 bool has_video = false;
244 for (size_t i = 0; i < codecs.size(); ++i) {
245 if (!codecs[i].ValidateCodecFormat()) {
246 return false;
247 }
248 if (codecs[i].GetCodecType() == VideoCodec::CODEC_VIDEO) {
249 has_video = true;
250 }
251 }
252 if (!has_video) {
253 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Setting codecs without a video codec is invalid: "
254 << CodecVectorToString(codecs);
255 return false;
256 }
257 return true;
258}
259
260static bool ValidateStreamParams(const StreamParams& sp) {
261 if (sp.ssrcs.empty()) {
262 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "No SSRCs in stream parameters: " << sp.ToString();
263 return false;
264 }
265
266 std::vector<uint32_t> primary_ssrcs;
267 sp.GetPrimarySsrcs(&primary_ssrcs);
268 std::vector<uint32_t> rtx_ssrcs;
269 sp.GetFidSsrcs(primary_ssrcs, &rtx_ssrcs);
270 for (uint32_t rtx_ssrc : rtx_ssrcs) {
271 bool rtx_ssrc_present = false;
272 for (uint32_t sp_ssrc : sp.ssrcs) {
273 if (sp_ssrc == rtx_ssrc) {
274 rtx_ssrc_present = true;
275 break;
276 }
277 }
278 if (!rtx_ssrc_present) {
279 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "RTX SSRC '" << rtx_ssrc
280 << "' missing from StreamParams ssrcs: "
281 << sp.ToString();
282 return false;
283 }
284 }
285 if (!rtx_ssrcs.empty() && primary_ssrcs.size() != rtx_ssrcs.size()) {
286 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
287 << "RTX SSRCs exist, but don't cover all SSRCs (unsupported): "
288 << sp.ToString();
289 return false;
290 }
291
292 return true;
293}

295// Returns true if the given codec is disallowed from doing simulcast.
296bool IsCodecDisabledForSimulcast(const std::string& codec_name,
297 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
298 return !absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup("WebRTC-H264Simulcast"), "Disabled")
299 ? absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec_name, kVp9CodecName)
300 : absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec_name, kH264CodecName) ||
301 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec_name, kVp9CodecName);
302}

304// The selected thresholds for QVGA and VGA corresponded to a QP around 10.
305// The change in QP declined above the selected bitrates.
306static int GetMaxDefaultVideoBitrateKbps(int width,
307 int height,
308 bool is_screenshare) {
309 int max_bitrate;
310 if (width * height <= 320 * 240) {
311 max_bitrate = 600;
312 } else if (width * height <= 640 * 480) {
313 max_bitrate = 1700;
314 } else if (width * height <= 960 * 540) {
315 max_bitrate = 2000;
316 } else {
317 max_bitrate = 2500;
318 }
319 if (is_screenshare)
320 max_bitrate = std::max(max_bitrate, 1200);
321 return max_bitrate;
322}

324bool GetVp9LayersFromFieldTrialGroup(
325 size_t* num_spatial_layers,
326 size_t* num_temporal_layers,
327 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
328 std::string group = trials.Lookup("WebRTC-SupportVP9SVC");
329 if (group.empty())
330 return false;
331
332 if (sscanf(group.c_str(), "EnabledByFlag_%zuSL%zuTL", num_spatial_layers,
333 num_temporal_layers) != 2) {
334 return false;
335 }
336 if (*num_spatial_layers > webrtc::kMaxSpatialLayers ||
337 *num_spatial_layers < 1)
338 return false;
339
340 const size_t kMaxTemporalLayers = 3;
341 if (*num_temporal_layers > kMaxTemporalLayers || *num_temporal_layers < 1)
342 return false;
343
344 return true;
345}

347absl::optional<size_t> GetVp9SpatialLayersFromFieldTrial(
348 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
349 size_t num_sl;
350 size_t num_tl;
351 if (GetVp9LayersFromFieldTrialGroup(&num_sl, &num_tl, trials)) {
352 return num_sl;
353 }
354 return absl::nullopt;
355}

357absl::optional<size_t> GetVp9TemporalLayersFromFieldTrial(
358 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
359 size_t num_sl;
360 size_t num_tl;
361 if (GetVp9LayersFromFieldTrialGroup(&num_sl, &num_tl, trials)) {
362 return num_tl;
363 }
364 return absl::nullopt;
365}

367// Returns its smallest positive argument. If neither argument is positive,
368// returns an arbitrary nonpositive value.
369int MinPositive(int a, int b) {
370 if (a <= 0) {
371 return b;
372 }
373 if (b <= 0) {
374 return a;
375 }
376 return std::min(a, b);
377}

379bool IsLayerActive(const webrtc::RtpEncodingParameters& layer) {
380 return layer.active &&
381 (!layer.max_bitrate_bps || *layer.max_bitrate_bps > 0) &&
382 (!layer.max_framerate || *layer.max_framerate > 0);
383}
384
385size_t FindRequiredActiveLayers(
386 const webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig& encoder_config) {
387 // Need enough layers so that at least the first active one is present.
388 for (size_t i = 0; i < encoder_config.number_of_streams; ++i) {
389 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].active) {
390 return i + 1;
391 }
392 }
393 return 0;
394}
395
396int NumActiveStreams(const webrtc::RtpParameters& rtp_parameters) {
397 int res = 0;
398 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_parameters.encodings.size(); ++i) {
399 if (rtp_parameters.encodings[i].active) {
400 ++res;
401 }
402 }
403 return res;
404}

406std::map<uint32_t, webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats>
407MergeInfoAboutOutboundRtpSubstreams(
408 const std::map<uint32_t, webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats>&
409 substreams) {
410 std::map<uint32_t, webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats> rtp_substreams;
411 // Add substreams for all RTP media streams.
412 for (const auto& pair : substreams) {
413 uint32_t ssrc = pair.first;
414 const webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats& substream = pair.second;
415 switch (substream.type) {
416 case webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kMedia:
417 break;
418 case webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kRtx:
419 case webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kFlexfec:
420 continue;
421 }
422 rtp_substreams.insert(std::make_pair(ssrc, substream));
423 }
424 // Complement the kMedia substream stats with the associated kRtx and kFlexfec
425 // substream stats.
426 for (const auto& pair : substreams) {
427 switch (pair.second.type) {
428 case webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kMedia:
429 continue;
430 case webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kRtx:
431 case webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kFlexfec:
432 break;
433 }
434 // The associated substream is an RTX or FlexFEC substream that is
435 // referencing an RTP media substream.
436 const webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats& associated_substream =
437 pair.second;
438 RTC_DCHECK(associated_substream.referenced_media_ssrc.has_value());
439 uint32_t media_ssrc = associated_substream.referenced_media_ssrc.value();
440 if (substreams.find(media_ssrc) == substreams.end()) {
441 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Substream [ssrc: " << pair.first << ", type: "
442 << StreamTypeToString(associated_substream.type)
443 << "] is associated with a media ssrc (" << media_ssrc
444 << ") that does not have StreamStats. Ignoring its "
445 << "RTP stats.";
446 continue;
447 }
448 webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats& rtp_substream =
449 rtp_substreams[media_ssrc];
450
451 // We only merge |rtp_stats|. All other metrics are not applicable for RTX
452 // and FlexFEC.
453 // TODO(hbos): kRtx and kFlexfec stats should use a separate struct to make
454 // it clear what is or is not applicable.
455 rtp_substream.rtp_stats.Add(associated_substream.rtp_stats);
456 }
457 return rtp_substreams;
458}

478rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig::EncoderSpecificSettings>
479WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::ConfigureVideoEncoderSettings(
480 const VideoCodec& codec) {
481 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
482 bool is_screencast = parameters_.options.is_screencast.value_or(false);
483 // No automatic resizing when using simulcast or screencast, or when
484 // disabled by field trial flag.
485 bool automatic_resize = !disable_automatic_resize_ && !is_screencast &&
486 (parameters_.config.rtp.ssrcs.size() == 1 ||
487 NumActiveStreams(rtp_parameters_) == 1);
488
489 bool frame_dropping = !is_screencast;
490 bool denoising;
491 bool codec_default_denoising = false;
492 if (is_screencast) {
493 denoising = false;
494 } else {
495 // Use codec default if video_noise_reduction is unset.
496 codec_default_denoising = !parameters_.options.video_noise_reduction;
497 denoising = parameters_.options.video_noise_reduction.value_or(false);
498 }
499
500 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, kH264CodecName)) {
501 webrtc::VideoCodecH264 h264_settings =
502 webrtc::VideoEncoder::GetDefaultH264Settings();
503 h264_settings.frameDroppingOn = frame_dropping;
504 return rtc::make_ref_counted<
505 webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig::H264EncoderSpecificSettings>(h264_settings);
506 }
507 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, kVp8CodecName)) {
508 webrtc::VideoCodecVP8 vp8_settings =
509 webrtc::VideoEncoder::GetDefaultVp8Settings();
510 vp8_settings.automaticResizeOn = automatic_resize;
511 // VP8 denoising is enabled by default.
512 vp8_settings.denoisingOn = codec_default_denoising ? true : denoising;
513 vp8_settings.frameDroppingOn = frame_dropping;
514 return rtc::make_ref_counted<
515 webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig::Vp8EncoderSpecificSettings>(vp8_settings);
516 }
517 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, kVp9CodecName)) {
518 webrtc::VideoCodecVP9 vp9_settings =
519 webrtc::VideoEncoder::GetDefaultVp9Settings();
520 const size_t default_num_spatial_layers =
521 parameters_.config.rtp.ssrcs.size();
522 const size_t num_spatial_layers =
523 GetVp9SpatialLayersFromFieldTrial(call_->trials())
524 .value_or(default_num_spatial_layers);
525
526 const size_t default_num_temporal_layers =
527 num_spatial_layers > 1 ? kConferenceDefaultNumTemporalLayers : 1;
528 const size_t num_temporal_layers =
529 GetVp9TemporalLayersFromFieldTrial(call_->trials())
530 .value_or(default_num_temporal_layers);
531
532 vp9_settings.numberOfSpatialLayers = std::min<unsigned char>(
533 num_spatial_layers, kConferenceMaxNumSpatialLayers);
534 vp9_settings.numberOfTemporalLayers = std::min<unsigned char>(
535 num_temporal_layers, kConferenceMaxNumTemporalLayers);
536
537 // VP9 denoising is disabled by default.
538 vp9_settings.denoisingOn = codec_default_denoising ? true : denoising;
539 vp9_settings.automaticResizeOn = automatic_resize;
540 // Ensure frame dropping is always enabled.
541 RTC_DCHECK(vp9_settings.frameDroppingOn);
542 if (!is_screencast) {
543 webrtc::FieldTrialFlag interlayer_pred_experiment_enabled =
544 webrtc::FieldTrialFlag("Enabled");
545 webrtc::FieldTrialEnum<webrtc::InterLayerPredMode> inter_layer_pred_mode(
546 "inter_layer_pred_mode", webrtc::InterLayerPredMode::kOnKeyPic,
547 {{"off", webrtc::InterLayerPredMode::kOff},
548 {"on", webrtc::InterLayerPredMode::kOn},
549 {"onkeypic", webrtc::InterLayerPredMode::kOnKeyPic}});
550 webrtc::ParseFieldTrial(
551 {&interlayer_pred_experiment_enabled, &inter_layer_pred_mode},
552 call_->trials().Lookup("WebRTC-Vp9InterLayerPred"));
553 if (interlayer_pred_experiment_enabled) {
554 vp9_settings.interLayerPred = inter_layer_pred_mode;
555 } else {
556 // Limit inter-layer prediction to key pictures by default.
557 vp9_settings.interLayerPred = webrtc::InterLayerPredMode::kOnKeyPic;
558 }
559 } else {
560 // Multiple spatial layers vp9 screenshare needs flexible mode.
561 vp9_settings.flexibleMode = vp9_settings.numberOfSpatialLayers > 1;
562 vp9_settings.interLayerPred = webrtc::InterLayerPredMode::kOn;
563 }
564 return rtc::make_ref_counted<
565 webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig::Vp9EncoderSpecificSettings>(vp9_settings);
566 }
567 return nullptr;
568}

570DefaultUnsignalledSsrcHandler::DefaultUnsignalledSsrcHandler()
571 : default_sink_(nullptr) {}
572
573UnsignalledSsrcHandler::Action DefaultUnsignalledSsrcHandler::OnUnsignalledSsrc(
574 WebRtcVideoChannel* channel,
575 uint32_t ssrc) {
576 absl::optional<uint32_t> default_recv_ssrc =
577 channel->GetDefaultReceiveStreamSsrc();
578
579 if (default_recv_ssrc) {
580 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Destroying old default receive stream for SSRC="
581 << ssrc << ".";
582 channel->RemoveRecvStream(*default_recv_ssrc);
583 }
584
585 StreamParams sp = channel->unsignaled_stream_params();
586 sp.ssrcs.push_back(ssrc);
587
588 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Creating default receive stream for SSRC=" << ssrc
589 << ".";
590 if (!channel->AddRecvStream(sp, /*default_stream=*/true)) {
591 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Could not create default receive stream.";
592 }
593
594 // SSRC 0 returns default_recv_base_minimum_delay_ms.
595 const int unsignaled_ssrc = 0;
596 int default_recv_base_minimum_delay_ms =
597 channel->GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(unsignaled_ssrc).value_or(0);
598 // Set base minimum delay if it was set before for the default receive stream.
599 channel->SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(ssrc,
600 default_recv_base_minimum_delay_ms);
601 channel->SetSink(ssrc, default_sink_);
602 return kDeliverPacket;
603}

656std::vector<webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability>
657WebRtcVideoEngine::GetRtpHeaderExtensions() const {
658 std::vector<webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability> result;
659 int id = 1;
660 for (const auto& uri :
661 {webrtc::RtpExtension::kTimestampOffsetUri,
662 webrtc::RtpExtension::kAbsSendTimeUri,
663 webrtc::RtpExtension::kVideoRotationUri,
664 webrtc::RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberUri,
665 webrtc::RtpExtension::kPlayoutDelayUri,
666 webrtc::RtpExtension::kVideoContentTypeUri,
667 webrtc::RtpExtension::kVideoTimingUri,
668 webrtc::RtpExtension::kColorSpaceUri, webrtc::RtpExtension::kMidUri,
669 webrtc::RtpExtension::kRidUri, webrtc::RtpExtension::kRepairedRidUri}) {
670 result.emplace_back(uri, id++, webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv);
671 }
672 result.emplace_back(webrtc::RtpExtension::kGenericFrameDescriptorUri00, id++,
673 IsEnabled(trials_, "WebRTC-GenericDescriptorAdvertised")
674 ? webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv
675 : webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped);
676 result.emplace_back(
677 webrtc::RtpExtension::kDependencyDescriptorUri, id++,
678 IsEnabled(trials_, "WebRTC-DependencyDescriptorAdvertised")
679 ? webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv
680 : webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped);
681
682 result.emplace_back(
683 webrtc::RtpExtension::kVideoLayersAllocationUri, id++,
684 IsEnabled(trials_, "WebRTC-VideoLayersAllocationAdvertised")
685 ? webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv
686 : webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped);
687
688 result.emplace_back(
689 webrtc::RtpExtension::kVideoFrameTrackingIdUri, id++,
690 IsEnabled(trials_, "WebRTC-VideoFrameTrackingIdAdvertised")
691 ? webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv
692 : webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped);
693
694 return result;
695}

741
742std::vector<WebRtcVideoChannel::VideoCodecSettings>
743WebRtcVideoChannel::SelectSendVideoCodecs(
744 const std::vector<VideoCodecSettings>& remote_mapped_codecs) const {
745 std::vector<webrtc::SdpVideoFormat> sdp_formats =
746 encoder_factory_ ? encoder_factory_->GetImplementations()
747 : std::vector<webrtc::SdpVideoFormat>();
748
749 // The returned vector holds the VideoCodecSettings in term of preference.
750 // They are orderd by receive codec preference first and local implementation
751 // preference second.
752 std::vector<VideoCodecSettings> encoders;
753 for (const VideoCodecSettings& remote_codec : remote_mapped_codecs) {
754 for (auto format_it = sdp_formats.begin();
755 format_it != sdp_formats.end();) {
756 // For H264, we will limit the encode level to the remote offered level
757 // regardless if level asymmetry is allowed or not. This is strictly not
758 // following the spec in https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6184#section-8.2.2
759 // since we should limit the encode level to the lower of local and remote
760 // level when level asymmetry is not allowed.
761 if (format_it->IsSameCodec(
762 {remote_codec.codec.name, remote_codec.codec.params})) {
763 encoders.push_back(remote_codec);
764
765 // To allow the VideoEncoderFactory to keep information about which
766 // implementation to instantitate when CreateEncoder is called the two
767 // parmeter sets are merged.
768 encoders.back().codec.params.insert(format_it->parameters.begin(),
769 format_it->parameters.end());
770
771 format_it = sdp_formats.erase(format_it);
772 } else {
773 ++format_it;
774 }
775 }
776 }
777
778 return encoders;
779}
780
781bool WebRtcVideoChannel::NonFlexfecReceiveCodecsHaveChanged(
782 std::vector<VideoCodecSettings> before,
783 std::vector<VideoCodecSettings> after) {
784 // The receive codec order doesn't matter, so we sort the codecs before
785 // comparing. This is necessary because currently the
786 // only way to change the send codec is to munge SDP, which causes
787 // the receive codec list to change order, which causes the streams
788 // to be recreates which causes a "blink" of black video. In order
789 // to support munging the SDP in this way without recreating receive
790 // streams, we ignore the order of the received codecs so that
791 // changing the order doesn't cause this "blink".
792 auto comparison = [](const VideoCodecSettings& codec1,
793 const VideoCodecSettings& codec2) {
794 return codec1.codec.id > codec2.codec.id;
795 };
796 absl::c_sort(before, comparison);
797 absl::c_sort(after, comparison);
798
799 // Changes in FlexFEC payload type are handled separately in
800 // WebRtcVideoChannel::GetChangedRecvParameters, so disregard FlexFEC in the
801 // comparison here.
802 return !absl::c_equal(before, after,
803 VideoCodecSettings::EqualsDisregardingFlexfec);
804}
805
806bool WebRtcVideoChannel::GetChangedSendParameters(
807 const VideoSendParameters& params,
808 ChangedSendParameters* changed_params) const {
809 if (!ValidateCodecFormats(params.codecs) ||
810 !ValidateRtpExtensions(params.extensions)) {
811 return false;
812 }
813
814 std::vector<VideoCodecSettings> negotiated_codecs =
815 SelectSendVideoCodecs(MapCodecs(params.codecs));
816
817 // We should only fail here if send direction is enabled.
818 if (params.is_stream_active && negotiated_codecs.empty()) {
819 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "No video codecs supported.";
820 return false;
821 }
822
823 // Never enable sending FlexFEC, unless we are in the experiment.
824 if (!IsEnabled(call_->trials(), "WebRTC-FlexFEC-03")) {
825 for (VideoCodecSettings& codec : negotiated_codecs)
826 codec.flexfec_payload_type = -1;
827 }
828
829 if (negotiated_codecs_ != negotiated_codecs) {
830 if (negotiated_codecs.empty()) {
831 changed_params->send_codec = absl::nullopt;
832 } else if (send_codec_ != negotiated_codecs.front()) {
833 changed_params->send_codec = negotiated_codecs.front();
834 }
835 changed_params->negotiated_codecs = std::move(negotiated_codecs);
836 }
837
838 // Handle RTP header extensions.
839 if (params.extmap_allow_mixed != ExtmapAllowMixed()) {
840 changed_params->extmap_allow_mixed = params.extmap_allow_mixed;
841 }
842 std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension> filtered_extensions = FilterRtpExtensions(
843 params.extensions, webrtc::RtpExtension::IsSupportedForVideo, true,
844 call_->trials());
845 if (!send_rtp_extensions_ || (*send_rtp_extensions_ != filtered_extensions)) {
846 changed_params->rtp_header_extensions =
847 absl::optional<std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension>>(filtered_extensions);
848 }
849
850 if (params.mid != send_params_.mid) {
851 changed_params->mid = params.mid;
852 }
853
854 // Handle max bitrate.
855 if (params.max_bandwidth_bps != send_params_.max_bandwidth_bps &&
856 params.max_bandwidth_bps >= -1) {
857 // 0 or -1 uncaps max bitrate.
858 // TODO(pbos): Reconsider how 0 should be treated. It is not mentioned as a
859 // special value and might very well be used for stopping sending.
860 changed_params->max_bandwidth_bps =
861 params.max_bandwidth_bps == 0 ? -1 : params.max_bandwidth_bps;
862 }
863
864 // Handle conference mode.
865 if (params.conference_mode != send_params_.conference_mode) {
866 changed_params->conference_mode = params.conference_mode;
867 }
868
869 // Handle RTCP mode.
870 if (params.rtcp.reduced_size != send_params_.rtcp.reduced_size) {
871 changed_params->rtcp_mode = params.rtcp.reduced_size
872 ? webrtc::RtcpMode::kReducedSize
873 : webrtc::RtcpMode::kCompound;
874 }
875
876 return true;
877}
878
879bool WebRtcVideoChannel::SetSendParameters(const VideoSendParameters& params) {
880 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
881 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVideoChannel::SetSendParameters");
882 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "SetSendParameters: " << params.ToString();
883 ChangedSendParameters changed_params;
884 if (!GetChangedSendParameters(params, &changed_params)) {
885 return false;
886 }
887
888 if (changed_params.negotiated_codecs) {
889 for (const auto& send_codec : *changed_params.negotiated_codecs)
890 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Negotiated codec: " << send_codec.codec.ToString();
891 }
892
893 send_params_ = params;
894 return ApplyChangedParams(changed_params);
895}
896
897void WebRtcVideoChannel::RequestEncoderFallback() {
898 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
899 if (negotiated_codecs_.size() <= 1) {
900 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Encoder failed but no fallback codec is available";
901 return;
902 }
903
904 ChangedSendParameters params;
905 params.negotiated_codecs = negotiated_codecs_;
906 params.negotiated_codecs->erase(params.negotiated_codecs->begin());
907 params.send_codec = params.negotiated_codecs->front();
908 ApplyChangedParams(params);
909}
910
911void WebRtcVideoChannel::RequestEncoderSwitch(
912 const EncoderSwitchRequestCallback::Config& conf) {
913 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
914
915 if (!allow_codec_switching_) {
916 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Encoder switch requested but codec switching has"
917 " not been enabled yet.";
918 requested_encoder_switch_ = conf;
919 return;
920 }
921
922 for (const VideoCodecSettings& codec_setting : negotiated_codecs_) {
923 if (codec_setting.codec.name == conf.codec_name) {
924 if (conf.param) {
925 auto it = codec_setting.codec.params.find(*conf.param);
926 if (it == codec_setting.codec.params.end())
927 continue;
928
929 if (conf.value && it->second != *conf.value)
930 continue;
931 }
932
933 if (send_codec_ == codec_setting) {
934 // Already using this codec, no switch required.
935 return;
936 }
937
938 ChangedSendParameters params;
939 params.send_codec = codec_setting;
940 ApplyChangedParams(params);
941 return;
942 }
943 }
944
945 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Requested encoder with codec_name:" << conf.codec_name
946 << ", param:" << conf.param.value_or("none")
947 << " and value:" << conf.value.value_or("none")
948 << "not found. No switch performed.";
949}
950
951void WebRtcVideoChannel::RequestEncoderSwitch(
952 const webrtc::SdpVideoFormat& format) {
953 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
954
955 for (const VideoCodecSettings& codec_setting : negotiated_codecs_) {
956 if (format.IsSameCodec(
957 {codec_setting.codec.name, codec_setting.codec.params})) {
958 VideoCodecSettings new_codec_setting = codec_setting;
959 for (const auto& kv : format.parameters) {
960 new_codec_setting.codec.params[kv.first] = kv.second;
961 }
962
963 if (send_codec_ == new_codec_setting) {
964 // Already using this codec, no switch required.
965 return;
966 }
967
968 ChangedSendParameters params;
969 params.send_codec = new_codec_setting;
970 ApplyChangedParams(params);
971 return;
972 }
973 }
974
975 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Encoder switch failed: SdpVideoFormat "
976 << format.ToString() << " not negotiated.";
977}
978
979bool WebRtcVideoChannel::ApplyChangedParams(
980 const ChangedSendParameters& changed_params) {
981 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
982 if (changed_params.negotiated_codecs)
983 negotiated_codecs_ = *changed_params.negotiated_codecs;
984
985 if (changed_params.send_codec)
986 send_codec_ = changed_params.send_codec;
987
988 if (changed_params.extmap_allow_mixed) {
989 SetExtmapAllowMixed(*changed_params.extmap_allow_mixed);
990 }
991 if (changed_params.rtp_header_extensions) {
992 send_rtp_extensions_ = changed_params.rtp_header_extensions;
993 }
994
995 if (changed_params.send_codec || changed_params.max_bandwidth_bps) {
996 if (send_params_.max_bandwidth_bps == -1) {
997 // Unset the global max bitrate (max_bitrate_bps) if max_bandwidth_bps is
998 // -1, which corresponds to no "b=AS" attribute in SDP. Note that the
999 // global max bitrate may be set below in GetBitrateConfigForCodec, from
1000 // the codec max bitrate.
1001 // TODO(pbos): This should be reconsidered (codec max bitrate should
1002 // probably not affect global call max bitrate).
1003 bitrate_config_.max_bitrate_bps = -1;
1004 }
1005
1006 if (send_codec_) {
1007 // TODO(holmer): Changing the codec parameters shouldn't necessarily mean
1008 // that we change the min/max of bandwidth estimation. Reevaluate this.
1009 bitrate_config_ = GetBitrateConfigForCodec(send_codec_->codec);
1010 if (!changed_params.send_codec) {
1011 // If the codec isn't changing, set the start bitrate to -1 which means
1012 // "unchanged" so that BWE isn't affected.
1013 bitrate_config_.start_bitrate_bps = -1;
1014 }
1015 }
1016
1017 if (send_params_.max_bandwidth_bps >= 0) {
1018 // Note that max_bandwidth_bps intentionally takes priority over the
1019 // bitrate config for the codec. This allows FEC to be applied above the
1020 // codec target bitrate.
1021 // TODO(pbos): Figure out whether b=AS means max bitrate for this
1022 // WebRtcVideoChannel (in which case we're good), or per sender (SSRC),
1023 // in which case this should not set a BitrateConstraints but rather
1024 // reconfigure all senders.
1025 bitrate_config_.max_bitrate_bps = send_params_.max_bandwidth_bps == 0
1026 ? -1
1027 : send_params_.max_bandwidth_bps;
1028 }
1029
1030 call_->GetTransportControllerSend()->SetSdpBitrateParameters(
1031 bitrate_config_);
1032 }
1033
1034 for (auto& kv : send_streams_) {
1035 kv.second->SetSendParameters(changed_params);
1036 }
1037 if (changed_params.send_codec || changed_params.rtcp_mode) {
1038 // Update receive feedback parameters from new codec or RTCP mode.
1039 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
1040 << "SetFeedbackParameters on all the receive streams because the send "
1041 "codec or RTCP mode has changed.";
1042 for (auto& kv : receive_streams_) {
1043 RTC_DCHECK(kv.second != nullptr);
1044 kv.second->SetFeedbackParameters(
1045 HasLntf(send_codec_->codec), HasNack(send_codec_->codec),
1046 HasTransportCc(send_codec_->codec),
1047 send_params_.rtcp.reduced_size ? webrtc::RtcpMode::kReducedSize
1048 : webrtc::RtcpMode::kCompound,
1049 send_codec_->rtx_time);
1050 }
1051 }
1052 return true;
1053}
1054
1055webrtc::RtpParameters WebRtcVideoChannel::GetRtpSendParameters(
1056 uint32_t ssrc) const {
1057 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1058 auto it = send_streams_.find(ssrc);
1059 if (it == send_streams_.end()) {
1060 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Attempting to get RTP send parameters for stream "
1061 "with ssrc "
1062 << ssrc << " which doesn't exist.";
1063 return webrtc::RtpParameters();
1064 }
1065
1066 webrtc::RtpParameters rtp_params = it->second->GetRtpParameters();
1067 // Need to add the common list of codecs to the send stream-specific
1068 // RTP parameters.
1069 for (const VideoCodec& codec : send_params_.codecs) {
1070 rtp_params.codecs.push_back(codec.ToCodecParameters());
1071 }
1072 return rtp_params;
1073}
1074
1075webrtc::RTCError WebRtcVideoChannel::SetRtpSendParameters(
1076 uint32_t ssrc,
1077 const webrtc::RtpParameters& parameters) {
1078 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1079 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVideoChannel::SetRtpSendParameters");
1080 auto it = send_streams_.find(ssrc);
1081 if (it == send_streams_.end()) {
1082 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Attempting to set RTP send parameters for stream "
1083 "with ssrc "
1084 << ssrc << " which doesn't exist.";
1085 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR);
1086 }
1087
1088 // TODO(deadbeef): Handle setting parameters with a list of codecs in a
1089 // different order (which should change the send codec).
1090 webrtc::RtpParameters current_parameters = GetRtpSendParameters(ssrc);
1091 if (current_parameters.codecs != parameters.codecs) {
1092 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR) << "Using SetParameters to change the set of codecs "
1093 "is not currently supported.";
1094 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR);
1095 }
1096
1097 if (!parameters.encodings.empty()) {
1098 // Note that these values come from:
1099 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-tsvwg-rtcweb-qos-16#section-5
1100 // TODO(deadbeef): Change values depending on whether we are sending a
1101 // keyframe or non-keyframe.
1102 rtc::DiffServCodePoint new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_DEFAULT;
1103 switch (parameters.encodings[0].network_priority) {
1104 case webrtc::Priority::kVeryLow:
1105 new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_CS1;
1106 break;
1107 case webrtc::Priority::kLow:
1108 new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_DEFAULT;
1109 break;
1110 case webrtc::Priority::kMedium:
1111 new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_AF42;
1112 break;
1113 case webrtc::Priority::kHigh:
1114 new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_AF41;
1115 break;
1116 }
1117 SetPreferredDscp(new_dscp);
1118 }
1119
1120 return it->second->SetRtpParameters(parameters);
1121}
1122
1123webrtc::RtpParameters WebRtcVideoChannel::GetRtpReceiveParameters(
1124 uint32_t ssrc) const {
1125 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1126 webrtc::RtpParameters rtp_params;
1127 auto it = receive_streams_.find(ssrc);
1128 if (it == receive_streams_.end()) {
1129 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1130 << "Attempting to get RTP receive parameters for stream "
1131 "with SSRC "
1132 << ssrc << " which doesn't exist.";
1133 return webrtc::RtpParameters();
1134 }
1135 rtp_params = it->second->GetRtpParameters();
1136
1137 // Add codecs, which any stream is prepared to receive.
1138 for (const VideoCodec& codec : recv_params_.codecs) {
1139 rtp_params.codecs.push_back(codec.ToCodecParameters());
1140 }
1141
1142 return rtp_params;
1143}
1144
1145webrtc::RtpParameters WebRtcVideoChannel::GetDefaultRtpReceiveParameters()
1146 const {
1147 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1148 webrtc::RtpParameters rtp_params;
1149 if (!default_unsignalled_ssrc_handler_.GetDefaultSink()) {
1150 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Attempting to get RTP parameters for the default, "
1151 "unsignaled video receive stream, but not yet "
1152 "configured to receive such a stream.";
1153 return rtp_params;
1154 }
1155 rtp_params.encodings.emplace_back();
1156
1157 // Add codecs, which any stream is prepared to receive.
1158 for (const VideoCodec& codec : recv_params_.codecs) {
1159 rtp_params.codecs.push_back(codec.ToCodecParameters());
1160 }
1161
1162 return rtp_params;
1163}
1164
1165bool WebRtcVideoChannel::GetChangedRecvParameters(
1166 const VideoRecvParameters& params,
1167 ChangedRecvParameters* changed_params) const {
1168 if (!ValidateCodecFormats(params.codecs) ||
1169 !ValidateRtpExtensions(params.extensions)) {
1170 return false;
1171 }
1172
1173 // Handle receive codecs.
1174 const std::vector<VideoCodecSettings> mapped_codecs =
1175 MapCodecs(params.codecs);
1176 if (mapped_codecs.empty()) {
1177 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
1178 << "GetChangedRecvParameters called without any video codecs.";
1179 return false;
1180 }
1181
1182 // Verify that every mapped codec is supported locally.
1183 if (params.is_stream_active) {
1184 const std::vector<VideoCodec> local_supported_codecs =
1185 GetPayloadTypesAndDefaultCodecs(decoder_factory_,
1186 /*is_decoder_factory=*/true,
1187 call_->trials());
1188 for (const VideoCodecSettings& mapped_codec : mapped_codecs) {
1189 if (!FindMatchingCodec(local_supported_codecs, mapped_codec.codec)) {
1190 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
1191 << "GetChangedRecvParameters called with unsupported video codec: "
1192 << mapped_codec.codec.ToString();
1193 return false;
1194 }
1195 }
1196 }
1197
1198 if (NonFlexfecReceiveCodecsHaveChanged(recv_codecs_, mapped_codecs)) {
1199 changed_params->codec_settings =
1200 absl::optional<std::vector<VideoCodecSettings>>(mapped_codecs);
1201 }
1202
1203 // Handle RTP header extensions.
1204 std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension> filtered_extensions = FilterRtpExtensions(
1205 params.extensions, webrtc::RtpExtension::IsSupportedForVideo, false,
1206 call_->trials());
1207 if (filtered_extensions != recv_rtp_extensions_) {
1208 changed_params->rtp_header_extensions =
1209 absl::optional<std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension>>(filtered_extensions);
1210 }
1211
1212 int flexfec_payload_type = mapped_codecs.front().flexfec_payload_type;
1213 if (flexfec_payload_type != recv_flexfec_payload_type_) {
1214 changed_params->flexfec_payload_type = flexfec_payload_type;
1215 }
1216
1217 return true;
1218}
1219
1220bool WebRtcVideoChannel::SetRecvParameters(const VideoRecvParameters& params) {
1221 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1222 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVideoChannel::SetRecvParameters");
1223 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "SetRecvParameters: " << params.ToString();
1224 ChangedRecvParameters changed_params;
1225 if (!GetChangedRecvParameters(params, &changed_params)) {
1226 return false;
1227 }
1228 if (changed_params.flexfec_payload_type) {
1229 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "Changing FlexFEC payload type (recv) from "
1230 << recv_flexfec_payload_type_ << " to "
1231 << *changed_params.flexfec_payload_type;
1232 recv_flexfec_payload_type_ = *changed_params.flexfec_payload_type;
1233 }
1234 if (changed_params.rtp_header_extensions) {
1235 recv_rtp_extensions_ = *changed_params.rtp_header_extensions;
1236 }
1237 if (changed_params.codec_settings) {
1238 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "Changing recv codecs from "
1239 << CodecSettingsVectorToString(recv_codecs_) << " to "
1240 << CodecSettingsVectorToString(
1241 *changed_params.codec_settings);
1242 recv_codecs_ = *changed_params.codec_settings;
1243 }
1244
1245 for (auto& kv : receive_streams_) {
1246 kv.second->SetRecvParameters(changed_params);
1247 }
1248 recv_params_ = params;
1249 return true;
1250}

1252std::string WebRtcVideoChannel::CodecSettingsVectorToString(
1253 const std::vector<VideoCodecSettings>& codecs) {
1254 rtc::StringBuilder out;
1255 out << "{";
1256 for (size_t i = 0; i < codecs.size(); ++i) {
1257 out << codecs[i].codec.ToString();
1258 if (i != codecs.size() - 1) {
1259 out << ", ";
1260 }
1261 }
1262 out << "}";
1263 return out.Release();
1264}

1336
1337bool WebRtcVideoChannel::AddSendStream(const StreamParams& sp) {
1338 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1339 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "AddSendStream: " << sp.ToString();
1340 if (!ValidateStreamParams(sp))
1341 return false;
1342
1343 if (!ValidateSendSsrcAvailability(sp))
1344 return false;
1345
1346 for (uint32_t used_ssrc : sp.ssrcs)
1347 send_ssrcs_.insert(used_ssrc);
1348
1349 webrtc::VideoSendStream::Config config(this);
1350
1351 for (const RidDescription& rid : sp.rids()) {
1352 config.rtp.rids.push_back(rid.rid);
1353 }
1354
1355 config.suspend_below_min_bitrate = video_config_.suspend_below_min_bitrate;
1356 config.periodic_alr_bandwidth_probing =
1357 video_config_.periodic_alr_bandwidth_probing;
1358 config.encoder_settings.experiment_cpu_load_estimator =
1359 video_config_.experiment_cpu_load_estimator;
1360 config.encoder_settings.encoder_factory = encoder_factory_;
1361 config.encoder_settings.bitrate_allocator_factory =
1362 bitrate_allocator_factory_;
1363 config.encoder_settings.encoder_switch_request_callback = this;
1364 config.crypto_options = crypto_options_;
1365 config.rtp.extmap_allow_mixed = ExtmapAllowMixed();
1366 config.rtcp_report_interval_ms = video_config_.rtcp_report_interval_ms;
1367
1368 WebRtcVideoSendStream* stream = new WebRtcVideoSendStream(
1369 call_, sp, std::move(config), default_send_options_,
1370 video_config_.enable_cpu_adaptation, bitrate_config_.max_bitrate_bps,
1371 send_codec_, send_rtp_extensions_, send_params_);
1372
1373 uint32_t ssrc = sp.first_ssrc();
1374 RTC_DCHECK(ssrc != 0);
1375 send_streams_[ssrc] = stream;
1376
1377 if (rtcp_receiver_report_ssrc_ == kDefaultRtcpReceiverReportSsrc) {
1378 rtcp_receiver_report_ssrc_ = ssrc;
1379 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
1380 << "SetLocalSsrc on all the receive streams because we added "
1381 "a send stream.";
1382 for (auto& kv : receive_streams_)
1383 kv.second->SetLocalSsrc(ssrc);
1384 }
1385 if (sending_) {
1386 stream->SetSend(true);
1387 }
1388
1389 return true;
1390}
1391
1392bool WebRtcVideoChannel::RemoveSendStream(uint32_t ssrc) {
1393 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1394 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "RemoveSendStream: " << ssrc;
1395
1396 WebRtcVideoSendStream* removed_stream;
1397 std::map<uint32_t, WebRtcVideoSendStream*>::iterator it =
1398 send_streams_.find(ssrc);
1399 if (it == send_streams_.end()) {
1400 return false;
1401 }
1402
1403 for (uint32_t old_ssrc : it->second->GetSsrcs())
1404 send_ssrcs_.erase(old_ssrc);
1405
1406 removed_stream = it->second;
1407 send_streams_.erase(it);
1408
1409 // Switch receiver report SSRCs, the one in use is no longer valid.
1410 if (rtcp_receiver_report_ssrc_ == ssrc) {
1411 rtcp_receiver_report_ssrc_ = send_streams_.empty()
1412 ? kDefaultRtcpReceiverReportSsrc
1413 : send_streams_.begin()->first;
1414 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "SetLocalSsrc on all the receive streams because the "
1415 "previous local SSRC was removed.";
1416
1417 for (auto& kv : receive_streams_) {
1418 kv.second->SetLocalSsrc(rtcp_receiver_report_ssrc_);
1419 }
1420 }
1421
1422 delete removed_stream;
1423
1424 return true;
1425}

1427void WebRtcVideoChannel::DeleteReceiveStream(
1428 WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoReceiveStream* stream) {
1429 for (uint32_t old_ssrc : stream->GetSsrcs())
1430 receive_ssrcs_.erase(old_ssrc);
1431 delete stream;
1432}
1433
1434bool WebRtcVideoChannel::AddRecvStream(const StreamParams& sp) {
1435 return AddRecvStream(sp, false);
1436}
1437
1438bool WebRtcVideoChannel::AddRecvStream(const StreamParams& sp,
1439 bool default_stream) {
1440 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1441
1442 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "AddRecvStream"
1443 << (default_stream ? " (default stream)" : "") << ": "
1444 << sp.ToString();
1445 if (!sp.has_ssrcs()) {
1446 // This is a StreamParam with unsignaled SSRCs. Store it, so it can be used
1447 // later when we know the SSRC on the first packet arrival.
1448 unsignaled_stream_params_ = sp;
1449 return true;
1450 }
1451
1452 if (!ValidateStreamParams(sp))
1453 return false;
1454
1455 uint32_t ssrc = sp.first_ssrc();
1456
1457 // Remove running stream if this was a default stream.
1458 const auto& prev_stream = receive_streams_.find(ssrc);
1459 if (prev_stream != receive_streams_.end()) {
1460 if (default_stream || !prev_stream->second->IsDefaultStream()) {
1461 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Receive stream for SSRC '" << ssrc
1462 << "' already exists.";
1463 return false;
1464 }
1465 DeleteReceiveStream(prev_stream->second);
1466 receive_streams_.erase(prev_stream);
1467 }
1468
1469 if (!ValidateReceiveSsrcAvailability(sp))
1470 return false;
1471
1472 for (uint32_t used_ssrc : sp.ssrcs)
1473 receive_ssrcs_.insert(used_ssrc);
1474
1475 webrtc::VideoReceiveStream::Config config(this);
1476 webrtc::FlexfecReceiveStream::Config flexfec_config(this);
1477 ConfigureReceiverRtp(&config, &flexfec_config, sp);
1478
1479 config.crypto_options = crypto_options_;
1480 config.enable_prerenderer_smoothing =
1481 video_config_.enable_prerenderer_smoothing;
1482 if (!sp.stream_ids().empty()) {
1483 config.sync_group = sp.stream_ids()[0];
1484 }
1485
1486 if (unsignaled_frame_transformer_ && !config.frame_transformer)
1487 config.frame_transformer = unsignaled_frame_transformer_;
1488
1489 receive_streams_[ssrc] = new WebRtcVideoReceiveStream(
1490 this, call_, sp, std::move(config), decoder_factory_, default_stream,
1491 recv_codecs_, flexfec_config);
1492
1493 return true;
1494}
1495
1496void WebRtcVideoChannel::ConfigureReceiverRtp(
1497 webrtc::VideoReceiveStream::Config* config,
1498 webrtc::FlexfecReceiveStream::Config* flexfec_config,
1499 const StreamParams& sp) const {
1500 uint32_t ssrc = sp.first_ssrc();
1501
1502 config->rtp.remote_ssrc = ssrc;
1503 config->rtp.local_ssrc = rtcp_receiver_report_ssrc_;
1504
1505 // TODO(pbos): This protection is against setting the same local ssrc as
1506 // remote which is not permitted by the lower-level API. RTCP requires a
1507 // corresponding sender SSRC. Figure out what to do when we don't have
1508 // (receive-only) or know a good local SSRC.
1509 if (config->rtp.remote_ssrc == config->rtp.local_ssrc) {
1510 if (config->rtp.local_ssrc != kDefaultRtcpReceiverReportSsrc) {
1511 config->rtp.local_ssrc = kDefaultRtcpReceiverReportSsrc;
1512 } else {
1513 config->rtp.local_ssrc = kDefaultRtcpReceiverReportSsrc + 1;
1514 }
1515 }
1516
1517 // Whether or not the receive stream sends reduced size RTCP is determined
1518 // by the send params.
1519 // TODO(deadbeef): Once we change "send_params" to "sender_params" and
1520 // "recv_params" to "receiver_params", we should get this out of
1521 // receiver_params_.
1522 config->rtp.rtcp_mode = send_params_.rtcp.reduced_size
1523 ? webrtc::RtcpMode::kReducedSize
1524 : webrtc::RtcpMode::kCompound;
1525
1526 // rtx-time (RFC 4588) is a declarative attribute similar to rtcp-rsize and
1527 // determined by the sender / send codec.
1528 if (send_codec_ && send_codec_->rtx_time != -1) {
1529 config->rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms = send_codec_->rtx_time;
1530 }
1531
1532 config->rtp.transport_cc =
1533 send_codec_ ? HasTransportCc(send_codec_->codec) : false;
1534
1535 sp.GetFidSsrc(ssrc, &config->rtp.rtx_ssrc);
1536
1537 config->rtp.extensions = recv_rtp_extensions_;
1538
1539 // TODO(brandtr): Generalize when we add support for multistream protection.
1540 flexfec_config->payload_type = recv_flexfec_payload_type_;
1541 if (!IsDisabled(call_->trials(), "WebRTC-FlexFEC-03-Advertised") &&
1542 sp.GetFecFrSsrc(ssrc, &flexfec_config->remote_ssrc)) {
1543 flexfec_config->protected_media_ssrcs = {ssrc};
1544 flexfec_config->local_ssrc = config->rtp.local_ssrc;
1545 flexfec_config->rtcp_mode = config->rtp.rtcp_mode;
1546 // TODO(brandtr): We should be spec-compliant and set |transport_cc| here
1547 // based on the rtcp-fb for the FlexFEC codec, not the media codec.
1548 flexfec_config->transport_cc = config->rtp.transport_cc;
1549 flexfec_config->rtp_header_extensions = config->rtp.extensions;
1550 }
1551}

1553bool WebRtcVideoChannel::RemoveRecvStream(uint32_t ssrc) {
1554 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1555 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "RemoveRecvStream: " << ssrc;
1556
1557 std::map<uint32_t, WebRtcVideoReceiveStream*>::iterator stream =
1558 receive_streams_.find(ssrc);
1559 if (stream == receive_streams_.end()) {
1560 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Stream not found for ssrc: " << ssrc;
1561 return false;
1562 }
1563 DeleteReceiveStream(stream->second);
1564 receive_streams_.erase(stream);
1565
1566 return true;
1567}
1568
1569void WebRtcVideoChannel::ResetUnsignaledRecvStream() {
1570 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1571 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "ResetUnsignaledRecvStream.";
1572 unsignaled_stream_params_ = StreamParams();
1573
1574 // Delete any created default streams. This is needed to avoid SSRC collisions
1575 // in Call's RtpDemuxer, in the case that |this| has created a default video
1576 // receiver, and then some other WebRtcVideoChannel gets the SSRC signaled
1577 // in the corresponding Unified Plan "m=" section.
1578 auto it = receive_streams_.begin();
1579 while (it != receive_streams_.end()) {
1580 if (it->second->IsDefaultStream()) {
1581 DeleteReceiveStream(it->second);
1582 receive_streams_.erase(it++);
1583 } else {
1584 ++it;
1585 }
1586 }
1587}

1626bool WebRtcVideoChannel::GetStats(VideoMediaInfo* info) {
1627 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1628 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVideoChannel::GetStats");
1629
1630 // Log stats periodically.
1631 bool log_stats = false;
1632 int64_t now_ms = rtc::TimeMillis();
1633 if (last_stats_log_ms_ == -1 ||
1634 now_ms - last_stats_log_ms_ > kStatsLogIntervalMs) {
1635 last_stats_log_ms_ = now_ms;
1636 log_stats = true;
1637 }
1638
1639 info->Clear();
1640 FillSenderStats(info, log_stats);
1641 FillReceiverStats(info, log_stats);
1642 FillSendAndReceiveCodecStats(info);
1643 // TODO(holmer): We should either have rtt available as a metric on
1644 // VideoSend/ReceiveStreams, or we should remove rtt from VideoSenderInfo.
1645 webrtc::Call::Stats stats = call_->GetStats();
1646 if (stats.rtt_ms != -1) {
1647 for (size_t i = 0; i < info->senders.size(); ++i) {
1648 info->senders[i].rtt_ms = stats.rtt_ms;
1649 }
1650 for (size_t i = 0; i < info->aggregated_senders.size(); ++i) {
1651 info->aggregated_senders[i].rtt_ms = stats.rtt_ms;
1652 }
1653 }
1654
1655 if (log_stats)
1656 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << stats.ToString(now_ms);
1657
1658 return true;
1659}

1661void WebRtcVideoChannel::FillSenderStats(VideoMediaInfo* video_media_info,
1662 bool log_stats) {
1663 for (std::map<uint32_t, WebRtcVideoSendStream*>::iterator it =
1664 send_streams_.begin();
1665 it != send_streams_.end(); ++it) {
1666 auto infos = it->second->GetPerLayerVideoSenderInfos(log_stats);
1667 if (infos.empty())
1668 continue;
1669 video_media_info->aggregated_senders.push_back(
1670 it->second->GetAggregatedVideoSenderInfo(infos));
1671 for (auto&& info : infos) {
1672 video_media_info->senders.push_back(info);
1673 }
1674 }
1675}

1679 for (std::map<uint32_t, WebRtcVideoReceiveStream*>::iterator it =
1680 receive_streams_.begin();
1681 it != receive_streams_.end(); ++it) {
1682 video_media_info->receivers.push_back(
1683 it->second->GetVideoReceiverInfo(log_stats));

1696void WebRtcVideoChannel::FillSendAndReceiveCodecStats(

1698 for (const VideoCodec& codec : send_params_.codecs) {

1700 video_media_info->send_codecs.insert(

1709
1710void WebRtcVideoChannel::OnPacketReceived(rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer packet,
1711 int64_t packet_time_us) {
1712 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&network_thread_checker_);
1713 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): This code is very similar to what
1714 // WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::OnPacketReceived does. For maintainability and
1715 // consistency it would be good to move the interaction with call_->Receiver()
1716 // to a common implementation and provide a callback on the worker thread
1717 // for the exception case (DELIVERY_UNKNOWN_SSRC) and how retry is attempted.
1718 worker_thread_->PostTask(
1719 ToQueuedTask(task_safety_, [this, packet, packet_time_us] {
1720 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1721 const webrtc::PacketReceiver::DeliveryStatus delivery_result =
1722 call_->Receiver()->DeliverPacket(webrtc::MediaType::VIDEO, packet,
1723 packet_time_us);
1724 switch (delivery_result) {
1725 case webrtc::PacketReceiver::DELIVERY_OK:
1726 return;
1727 case webrtc::PacketReceiver::DELIVERY_PACKET_ERROR:
1728 return;
1729 case webrtc::PacketReceiver::DELIVERY_UNKNOWN_SSRC:
1730 break;
1731 }
1732
1733 uint32_t ssrc = 0;
1734 if (!GetRtpSsrc(packet.cdata(), packet.size(), &ssrc)) {
1735 return;
1736 }
1737
1738 if (unknown_ssrc_packet_buffer_) {
1739 unknown_ssrc_packet_buffer_->AddPacket(ssrc, packet_time_us, packet);
1740 return;
1741 }
1742
1743 if (discard_unknown_ssrc_packets_) {
1744 return;
1745 }
1746
1747 int payload_type = 0;
1748 if (!GetRtpPayloadType(packet.cdata(), packet.size(), &payload_type)) {
1749 return;
1750 }
1751
1752 // See if this payload_type is registered as one that usually gets its
1753 // own SSRC (RTX) or at least is safe to drop either way (FEC). If it
1754 // is, and it wasn't handled above by DeliverPacket, that means we don't
1755 // know what stream it associates with, and we shouldn't ever create an
1756 // implicit channel for these.
1757 for (auto& codec : recv_codecs_) {
1758 if (payload_type == codec.rtx_payload_type ||
1759 payload_type == codec.ulpfec.red_rtx_payload_type ||
1760 payload_type == codec.ulpfec.ulpfec_payload_type) {
1761 return;
1762 }
1763 }
1764 if (payload_type == recv_flexfec_payload_type_) {
1765 return;
1766 }
1767
1768 // Ignore unknown ssrcs if there is a demuxer criteria update pending.
1769 // During a demuxer update we may receive ssrcs that were recently
1770 // removed or we may receve ssrcs that were recently configured for a
1771 // different video channel.
1772 if (demuxer_criteria_id_ != demuxer_criteria_completed_id_) {
1773 return;
1774 }
1775
1776 switch (unsignalled_ssrc_handler_->OnUnsignalledSsrc(this, ssrc)) {
1777 case UnsignalledSsrcHandler::kDropPacket:
1778 return;
1779 case UnsignalledSsrcHandler::kDeliverPacket:
1780 break;
1781 }
1782
1783 if (call_->Receiver()->DeliverPacket(webrtc::MediaType::VIDEO, packet,
1784 packet_time_us) !=
1785 webrtc::PacketReceiver::DELIVERY_OK) {
1786 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to deliver RTP packet on re-delivery.";
1787 }
1788 }));
1789}
1790
1791void WebRtcVideoChannel::OnPacketSent(const rtc::SentPacket& sent_packet) {
1792 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&network_thread_checker_);
1793 // TODO(tommi): We shouldn't need to go through call_ to deliver this
1794 // notification. We should already have direct access to
1795 // video_send_delay_stats_ and transport_send_ptr_ via `stream_`.
1796 // So we should be able to remove OnSentPacket from Call and handle this per
1797 // channel instead. At the moment Call::OnSentPacket calls OnSentPacket for
1798 // the video stats, for all sent packets, including audio, which causes
1799 // unnecessary lookups.
1800 call_->OnSentPacket(sent_packet);
1801}
1802
1803void WebRtcVideoChannel::BackfillBufferedPackets(
1804 rtc::ArrayView<const uint32_t> ssrcs) {
1805 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1806 if (!unknown_ssrc_packet_buffer_) {
1807 return;
1808 }
1809
1810 int delivery_ok_cnt = 0;
1811 int delivery_unknown_ssrc_cnt = 0;
1812 int delivery_packet_error_cnt = 0;
1813 webrtc::PacketReceiver* receiver = this->call_->Receiver();
1814 unknown_ssrc_packet_buffer_->BackfillPackets(
1815 ssrcs, [&](uint32_t /*ssrc*/, int64_t packet_time_us,
1816 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer packet) {
1817 switch (receiver->DeliverPacket(webrtc::MediaType::VIDEO, packet,
1818 packet_time_us)) {
1819 case webrtc::PacketReceiver::DELIVERY_OK:
1820 delivery_ok_cnt++;
1821 break;
1822 case webrtc::PacketReceiver::DELIVERY_UNKNOWN_SSRC:
1823 delivery_unknown_ssrc_cnt++;
1824 break;
1825 case webrtc::PacketReceiver::DELIVERY_PACKET_ERROR:
1826 delivery_packet_error_cnt++;
1827 break;
1828 }
1829 });
1830 rtc::StringBuilder out;
1831 out << "[ ";
1832 for (uint32_t ssrc : ssrcs) {
1833 out << std::to_string(ssrc) << " ";
1834 }
1835 out << "]";
1836 auto level = rtc::LS_INFO;
1837 if (delivery_unknown_ssrc_cnt > 0 || delivery_packet_error_cnt > 0) {
1838 level = rtc::LS_ERROR;
1839 }
1840 int total =
1841 delivery_ok_cnt + delivery_unknown_ssrc_cnt + delivery_packet_error_cnt;
1842 RTC_LOG_V(level) << "Backfilled " << total
1843 << " packets for ssrcs: " << out.Release()
1844 << " ok: " << delivery_ok_cnt
1845 << " error: " << delivery_packet_error_cnt
1846 << " unknown: " << delivery_unknown_ssrc_cnt;
1847}

1871void WebRtcVideoChannel::SetInterface(NetworkInterface* iface) {
1872 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&network_thread_checker_);
1873 MediaChannel::SetInterface(iface);
1874 // Set the RTP recv/send buffer to a bigger size.
1875
1876 // The group should be a positive integer with an explicit size, in
1877 // which case that is used as UDP recevie buffer size. All other values shall
1878 // result in the default value being used.
1879 const std::string group_name_recv_buf_size =
1880 call_->trials().Lookup("WebRTC-IncreasedReceivebuffers");
1881 int recv_buffer_size = kVideoRtpRecvBufferSize;
1882 if (!group_name_recv_buf_size.empty() &&
1883 (sscanf(group_name_recv_buf_size.c_str(), "%d", &recv_buffer_size) != 1 ||
1884 recv_buffer_size <= 0)) {
1885 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid receive buffer size: "
1886 << group_name_recv_buf_size;
1887 recv_buffer_size = kVideoRtpRecvBufferSize;
1888 }
1889
1890 MediaChannel::SetOption(NetworkInterface::ST_RTP, rtc::Socket::OPT_RCVBUF,
1891 recv_buffer_size);
1892
1893 // Speculative change to increase the outbound socket buffer size.
1894 // In b/15152257, we are seeing a significant number of packets discarded
1895 // due to lack of socket buffer space, although it's not yet clear what the
1896 // ideal value should be.
1897 const std::string group_name_send_buf_size =
1898 call_->trials().Lookup("WebRTC-SendBufferSizeBytes");
1899 int send_buffer_size = kVideoRtpSendBufferSize;
1900 if (!group_name_send_buf_size.empty() &&
1901 (sscanf(group_name_send_buf_size.c_str(), "%d", &send_buffer_size) != 1 ||
1902 send_buffer_size <= 0)) {
1903 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid send buffer size: "
1904 << group_name_send_buf_size;
1905 send_buffer_size = kVideoRtpSendBufferSize;
1906 }
1907
1908 MediaChannel::SetOption(NetworkInterface::ST_RTP, rtc::Socket::OPT_SNDBUF,
1909 send_buffer_size);
1910}

1947bool WebRtcVideoChannel::SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(uint32_t ssrc,
1948 int delay_ms) {
1949 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1950 absl::optional<uint32_t> default_ssrc = GetDefaultReceiveStreamSsrc();
1951
1952 // SSRC of 0 represents the default receive stream.
1953 if (ssrc == 0) {
1954 default_recv_base_minimum_delay_ms_ = delay_ms;
1955 }
1956
1957 if (ssrc == 0 && !default_ssrc) {
1958 return true;
1959 }
1960
1961 if (ssrc == 0 && default_ssrc) {
1962 ssrc = default_ssrc.value();
1963 }
1964
1965 auto stream = receive_streams_.find(ssrc);
1966 if (stream != receive_streams_.end()) {
1967 stream->second->SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(delay_ms);
1968 return true;
1969 } else {
1970 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "No stream found to set base minimum playout delay";
1971 return false;
1972 }
1973}
1974
1975absl::optional<int> WebRtcVideoChannel::GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(
1976 uint32_t ssrc) const {
1977 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1978 // SSRC of 0 represents the default receive stream.
1979 if (ssrc == 0) {
1980 return default_recv_base_minimum_delay_ms_;
1981 }
1982
1983 auto stream = receive_streams_.find(ssrc);
1984 if (stream != receive_streams_.end()) {
1985 return stream->second->GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs();
1986 } else {
1987 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "No stream found to get base minimum playout delay";
1988 return absl::nullopt;
1989 }
1990}
1991
1992absl::optional<uint32_t> WebRtcVideoChannel::GetDefaultReceiveStreamSsrc() {
1993 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
1994 absl::optional<uint32_t> ssrc;
1995 for (auto it = receive_streams_.begin(); it != receive_streams_.end(); ++it) {
1996 if (it->second->IsDefaultStream()) {
1997 ssrc.emplace(it->first);
1998 break;
1999 }
2000 }
2001 return ssrc;
2002}

2166webrtc::DegradationPreference
2167WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::GetDegradationPreference() const {
2168 // Do not adapt resolution for screen content as this will likely
2169 // result in blurry and unreadable text.
2170 // |this| acts like a VideoSource to make sure SinkWants are handled on the
2171 // correct thread.
2172 if (!enable_cpu_overuse_detection_) {
2173 return webrtc::DegradationPreference::DISABLED;
2174 }
2175
2176 webrtc::DegradationPreference degradation_preference;
2177 if (rtp_parameters_.degradation_preference.has_value()) {
2178 degradation_preference = *rtp_parameters_.degradation_preference;
2179 } else {
2180 if (parameters_.options.content_hint ==
2181 webrtc::VideoTrackInterface::ContentHint::kFluid) {
2182 degradation_preference =
2183 webrtc::DegradationPreference::MAINTAIN_FRAMERATE;
2184 } else if (parameters_.options.is_screencast.value_or(false) ||
2185 parameters_.options.content_hint ==
2186 webrtc::VideoTrackInterface::ContentHint::kDetailed ||
2187 parameters_.options.content_hint ==
2188 webrtc::VideoTrackInterface::ContentHint::kText) {
2189 degradation_preference =
2190 webrtc::DegradationPreference::MAINTAIN_RESOLUTION;
2191 } else if (IsEnabled(call_->trials(), "WebRTC-Video-BalancedDegradation")) {
2192 // Standard wants balanced by default, but it needs to be tuned first.
2193 degradation_preference = webrtc::DegradationPreference::BALANCED;
2194 } else {
2195 // Keep MAINTAIN_FRAMERATE by default until BALANCED has been tuned for
2196 // all codecs and launched.
2197 degradation_preference =
2198 webrtc::DegradationPreference::MAINTAIN_FRAMERATE;
2199 }
2200 }
2201
2202 return degradation_preference;

2299webrtc::RTCError WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::SetRtpParameters(
2300 const webrtc::RtpParameters& new_parameters) {
2301 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
2302 webrtc::RTCError error = CheckRtpParametersInvalidModificationAndValues(
2303 rtp_parameters_, new_parameters);
2304 if (!error.ok()) {
2305 return error;
2306 }
2307
2308 bool new_param = false;
2309 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_parameters_.encodings.size(); ++i) {
2310 if ((new_parameters.encodings[i].min_bitrate_bps !=
2311 rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].min_bitrate_bps) ||
2312 (new_parameters.encodings[i].max_bitrate_bps !=
2313 rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].max_bitrate_bps) ||
2314 (new_parameters.encodings[i].max_framerate !=
2315 rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].max_framerate) ||
2316 (new_parameters.encodings[i].scale_resolution_down_by !=
2317 rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].scale_resolution_down_by) ||
2318 (new_parameters.encodings[i].num_temporal_layers !=
2319 rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].num_temporal_layers)) {
2320 new_param = true;
2321 break;
2322 }
2323 }
2324
2325 bool new_degradation_preference = false;
2326 if (new_parameters.degradation_preference !=
2327 rtp_parameters_.degradation_preference) {
2328 new_degradation_preference = true;
2329 }
2330
2331 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/8807): The bitrate priority really doesn't require an
2332 // entire encoder reconfiguration, it just needs to update the bitrate
2333 // allocator.
2334 bool reconfigure_encoder = new_param ||
2335 (new_parameters.encodings[0].bitrate_priority !=
2336 rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].bitrate_priority) ||
2337 new_parameters.encodings[0].scalability_mode !=
2338 rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].scalability_mode;
2339
2340 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/8807): The active field as well should not require
2341 // a full encoder reconfiguration, but it needs to update both the bitrate
2342 // allocator and the video bitrate allocator.
2343 //
2344 // Note that the simulcast encoder adapter relies on the fact that layers
2345 // de/activation triggers encoder reinitialization.
2346 bool new_send_state = false;
2347 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_parameters_.encodings.size(); ++i) {
2348 bool new_active = IsLayerActive(new_parameters.encodings[i]);
2349 bool old_active = IsLayerActive(rtp_parameters_.encodings[i]);
2350 if (new_active != old_active) {
2351 new_send_state = true;
2352 }
2353 }
2354 rtp_parameters_ = new_parameters;
2355 // Codecs are currently handled at the WebRtcVideoChannel level.
2356 rtp_parameters_.codecs.clear();
2357 if (reconfigure_encoder || new_send_state) {
2358 ReconfigureEncoder();
2359 }
2360 if (new_send_state) {
2361 UpdateSendState();
2362 }
2363 if (new_degradation_preference) {
2364 if (source_ && stream_) {
2365 stream_->SetSource(source_, GetDegradationPreference());
2366 }
2367 }
2368 return webrtc::RTCError::OK();
2369}

2371webrtc::RtpParameters
2372WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::GetRtpParameters() const {

2388
2389void WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::UpdateSendState() {
2390 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
2391 if (sending_) {
2392 RTC_DCHECK(stream_ != nullptr);
2393 size_t num_layers = rtp_parameters_.encodings.size();
2394 if (parameters_.encoder_config.number_of_streams == 1) {
2395 // SVC is used. Only one simulcast layer is present.
2396 num_layers = 1;
2397 }
2398 std::vector<bool> active_layers(num_layers);
2399 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_layers; ++i) {
2400 active_layers[i] = IsLayerActive(rtp_parameters_.encodings[i]);
2401 }
2402 if (parameters_.encoder_config.number_of_streams == 1 &&
2403 rtp_parameters_.encodings.size() > 1) {
2404 // SVC is used.
2405 // The only present simulcast layer should be active if any of the
2406 // configured SVC layers is active.
2407 active_layers[0] =
2408 absl::c_any_of(rtp_parameters_.encodings,
2409 [](const auto& encoding) { return encoding.active; });
2410 }
2411 // This updates what simulcast layers are sending, and possibly starts
2412 // or stops the VideoSendStream.
2413 stream_->UpdateActiveSimulcastLayers(active_layers);
2414 } else {
2415 if (stream_ != nullptr) {
2416 stream_->Stop();
2417 }
2418 }
2419}
2420
2421webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig
2422WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::CreateVideoEncoderConfig(
2423 const VideoCodec& codec) const {
2424 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
2425 webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig encoder_config;
2426 encoder_config.codec_type = webrtc::PayloadStringToCodecType(codec.name);
2427 encoder_config.video_format =
2428 webrtc::SdpVideoFormat(codec.name, codec.params);
2429
2430 bool is_screencast = parameters_.options.is_screencast.value_or(false);
2431 if (is_screencast) {
2432 encoder_config.min_transmit_bitrate_bps =
2433 1000 * parameters_.options.screencast_min_bitrate_kbps.value_or(0);
2434 encoder_config.content_type =
2435 webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kScreen;
2436 } else {
2437 encoder_config.min_transmit_bitrate_bps = 0;
2438 encoder_config.content_type =
2439 webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kRealtimeVideo;
2440 }
2441
2442 // By default, the stream count for the codec configuration should match the
2443 // number of negotiated ssrcs. But if the codec is disabled for simulcast
2444 // or a screencast (and not in simulcast screenshare experiment), only
2445 // configure a single stream.
2446 encoder_config.number_of_streams = parameters_.config.rtp.ssrcs.size();
2447 if (IsCodecDisabledForSimulcast(codec.name, call_->trials())) {
2448 encoder_config.number_of_streams = 1;
2449 }
2450
2451 // parameters_.max_bitrate comes from the max bitrate set at the SDP
2452 // (m-section) level with the attribute "b=AS." Note that we override this
2453 // value below if the RtpParameters max bitrate set with
2454 // RtpSender::SetParameters has a lower value.
2455 int stream_max_bitrate = parameters_.max_bitrate_bps;
2456 // When simulcast is enabled (when there are multiple encodings),
2457 // encodings[i].max_bitrate_bps will be enforced by
2458 // encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_bitrate_bps. Otherwise, it's
2459 // enforced by stream_max_bitrate, taking the minimum of the two maximums
2460 // (one coming from SDP, the other coming from RtpParameters).
2461 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].max_bitrate_bps &&
2462 rtp_parameters_.encodings.size() == 1) {
2463 stream_max_bitrate =
2464 MinPositive(*(rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].max_bitrate_bps),
2465 parameters_.max_bitrate_bps);
2466 }
2467
2468 // The codec max bitrate comes from the "x-google-max-bitrate" parameter
2469 // attribute set in the SDP for a specific codec. As done in
2470 // WebRtcVideoChannel::SetSendParameters, this value does not override the
2471 // stream max_bitrate set above.
2472 int codec_max_bitrate_kbps;
2473 if (codec.GetParam(kCodecParamMaxBitrate, &codec_max_bitrate_kbps) &&
2474 stream_max_bitrate == -1) {
2475 stream_max_bitrate = codec_max_bitrate_kbps * 1000;
2476 }
2477 encoder_config.max_bitrate_bps = stream_max_bitrate;
2478
2479 // The encoder config's default bitrate priority is set to 1.0,
2480 // unless it is set through the sender's encoding parameters.
2481 // The bitrate priority, which is used in the bitrate allocation, is done
2482 // on a per sender basis, so we use the first encoding's value.
2483 encoder_config.bitrate_priority =
2484 rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].bitrate_priority;
2485
2486 // Application-controlled state is held in the encoder_config's
2487 // simulcast_layers. Currently this is used to control which simulcast layers
2488 // are active and for configuring the min/max bitrate and max framerate.
2489 // The encoder_config's simulcast_layers is also used for non-simulcast (when
2490 // there is a single layer).
2491 RTC_DCHECK_GE(rtp_parameters_.encodings.size(),
2492 encoder_config.number_of_streams);
2493 RTC_DCHECK_GT(encoder_config.number_of_streams, 0);
2494
2495 // Copy all provided constraints.
2496 encoder_config.simulcast_layers.resize(rtp_parameters_.encodings.size());
2497 for (size_t i = 0; i < encoder_config.simulcast_layers.size(); ++i) {
2498 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].active =
2499 rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].active;
2500 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].scalability_mode =
2501 rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].scalability_mode;
2502 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].min_bitrate_bps) {
2503 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].min_bitrate_bps =
2504 *rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].min_bitrate_bps;
2505 }
2506 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].max_bitrate_bps) {
2507 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_bitrate_bps =
2508 *rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].max_bitrate_bps;
2509 }
2510 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].max_framerate) {
2511 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_framerate =
2512 *rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].max_framerate;
2513 }
2514 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].scale_resolution_down_by) {
2515 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].scale_resolution_down_by =
2516 *rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].scale_resolution_down_by;
2517 }
2518 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].num_temporal_layers) {
2519 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].num_temporal_layers =
2520 *rtp_parameters_.encodings[i].num_temporal_layers;
2521 }
2522 }
2523
2524 encoder_config.legacy_conference_mode = parameters_.conference_mode;
2525
2526 encoder_config.is_quality_scaling_allowed =
2527 !disable_automatic_resize_ && !is_screencast &&
2528 (parameters_.config.rtp.ssrcs.size() == 1 ||
2529 NumActiveStreams(rtp_parameters_) == 1);
2530
2531 int max_qp = kDefaultQpMax;
2532 codec.GetParam(kCodecParamMaxQuantization, &max_qp);
2533 encoder_config.video_stream_factory =
2534 rtc::make_ref_counted<EncoderStreamFactory>(
2535 codec.name, max_qp, is_screencast, parameters_.conference_mode);
2536
2537 return encoder_config;
2538}
