2572std::vector<VideoSenderInfo>
2573WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::GetPerLayerVideoSenderInfos(
2574 bool log_stats) {
2575 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
2576 VideoSenderInfo common_info;
2577 if (parameters_.codec_settings) {
2578 common_info.codec_name = parameters_.codec_settings->codec.name;
2579 common_info.codec_payload_type = parameters_.codec_settings->codec.id;
2580 }
2581 std::vector<VideoSenderInfo> infos;
2582 webrtc::VideoSendStream::Stats stats;
2583 if (stream_ == nullptr) {
2584 for (uint32_t ssrc : parameters_.config.rtp.ssrcs) {
2585 common_info.add_ssrc(ssrc);
2586 }
2587 infos.push_back(common_info);
2588 return infos;
2589 } else {
2590 stats = stream_->GetStats();
2591 if (log_stats)
2592 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << stats.ToString(rtc::TimeMillis());
2593
2594 // Metrics that are in common for all substreams.
2595 common_info.adapt_changes = stats.number_of_cpu_adapt_changes;
2596 common_info.adapt_reason =
2597 stats.cpu_limited_resolution ? ADAPTREASON_CPU : ADAPTREASON_NONE;
2598 common_info.has_entered_low_resolution = stats.has_entered_low_resolution;
2599
2600 // Get bandwidth limitation info from stream_->GetStats().
2601 // Input resolution (output from video_adapter) can be further scaled down
2602 // or higher video layer(s) can be dropped due to bitrate constraints.
2603 // Note, adapt_changes only include changes from the video_adapter.
2604 if (stats.bw_limited_resolution)
2605 common_info.adapt_reason |= ADAPTREASON_BANDWIDTH;
2606
2607 common_info.quality_limitation_reason = stats.quality_limitation_reason;
2608 common_info.quality_limitation_durations_ms =
2609 stats.quality_limitation_durations_ms;
2610 common_info.quality_limitation_resolution_changes =
2611 stats.quality_limitation_resolution_changes;
2612 common_info.encoder_implementation_name = stats.encoder_implementation_name;
2613 common_info.ssrc_groups = ssrc_groups_;
2614 common_info.frames = stats.frames;
2615 common_info.framerate_input = stats.input_frame_rate;
2616 common_info.avg_encode_ms = stats.avg_encode_time_ms;
2617 common_info.encode_usage_percent = stats.encode_usage_percent;
2618 common_info.nominal_bitrate = stats.media_bitrate_bps;
2619 common_info.content_type = stats.content_type;
2620 common_info.aggregated_framerate_sent = stats.encode_frame_rate;
2621 common_info.aggregated_huge_frames_sent = stats.huge_frames_sent;
2622
2623 // If we don't have any substreams, get the remaining metrics from |stats|.
2624 // Otherwise, these values are obtained from |sub_stream| below.
2625 if (stats.substreams.empty()) {
2626 for (uint32_t ssrc : parameters_.config.rtp.ssrcs) {
2627 common_info.add_ssrc(ssrc);
2628 }
2629 common_info.framerate_sent = stats.encode_frame_rate;
2630 common_info.frames_encoded = stats.frames_encoded;
2631 common_info.total_encode_time_ms = stats.total_encode_time_ms;
2632 common_info.total_encoded_bytes_target = stats.total_encoded_bytes_target;
2633 common_info.frames_sent = stats.frames_encoded;
2634 common_info.huge_frames_sent = stats.huge_frames_sent;
2635 infos.push_back(common_info);
2636 return infos;
2637 }
2638 }
2639 auto outbound_rtp_substreams =
2640 MergeInfoAboutOutboundRtpSubstreams(stats.substreams);
2641 for (const auto& pair : outbound_rtp_substreams) {
2642 auto info = common_info;
2643 info.add_ssrc(pair.first);
2644 info.rid = parameters_.config.rtp.GetRidForSsrc(pair.first);
2645 auto stream_stats = pair.second;
2646 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(stream_stats.type,
2647 webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats::StreamType::kMedia);
2648 info.payload_bytes_sent = stream_stats.rtp_stats.transmitted.payload_bytes;
2649 info.header_and_padding_bytes_sent =
2650 stream_stats.rtp_stats.transmitted.header_bytes +
2651 stream_stats.rtp_stats.transmitted.padding_bytes;
2652 info.packets_sent = stream_stats.rtp_stats.transmitted.packets;
2653 info.total_packet_send_delay_ms += stream_stats.total_packet_send_delay_ms;
2654 info.send_frame_width = stream_stats.width;
2655 info.send_frame_height = stream_stats.height;
2656 info.key_frames_encoded = stream_stats.frame_counts.key_frames;
2657 info.framerate_sent = stream_stats.encode_frame_rate;
2658 info.frames_encoded = stream_stats.frames_encoded;
2659 info.frames_sent = stream_stats.frames_encoded;
2660 info.retransmitted_bytes_sent =
2661 stream_stats.rtp_stats.retransmitted.payload_bytes;
2662 info.retransmitted_packets_sent =
2663 stream_stats.rtp_stats.retransmitted.packets;
2664 info.firs_rcvd = stream_stats.rtcp_packet_type_counts.fir_packets;
2665 info.nacks_rcvd = stream_stats.rtcp_packet_type_counts.nack_packets;
2666 info.plis_rcvd = stream_stats.rtcp_packet_type_counts.pli_packets;
2667 if (stream_stats.report_block_data.has_value()) {
2668 info.packets_lost =
2669 stream_stats.report_block_data->report_block().packets_lost;
2670 info.fraction_lost =
2671 static_cast<float>(
2672 stream_stats.report_block_data->report_block().fraction_lost) /
2673 (1 << 8);
2674 info.report_block_datas.push_back(*stream_stats.report_block_data);
2675 }
2676 info.qp_sum = stream_stats.qp_sum;
2677 info.total_encode_time_ms = stream_stats.total_encode_time_ms;
2678 info.total_encoded_bytes_target = stream_stats.total_encoded_bytes_target;
2679 info.huge_frames_sent = stream_stats.huge_frames_sent;
2680 infos.push_back(info);
2681 }
2682 return infos;
2683}
2684
2685VideoSenderInfo
2686WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::GetAggregatedVideoSenderInfo(
2687 const std::vector<VideoSenderInfo>& infos) const {
2688 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
2689 RTC_CHECK(!infos.empty());
2690 if (infos.size() == 1) {
2691 return infos[0];
2692 }
2693 VideoSenderInfo info = infos[0];
2694 info.local_stats.clear();
2695 for (uint32_t ssrc : parameters_.config.rtp.ssrcs) {
2696 info.add_ssrc(ssrc);
2697 }
2698 info.framerate_sent = info.aggregated_framerate_sent;
2699 info.huge_frames_sent = info.aggregated_huge_frames_sent;
2700
2701 for (size_t i = 1; i < infos.size(); i++) {
2702 info.key_frames_encoded += infos[i].key_frames_encoded;
2703 info.payload_bytes_sent += infos[i].payload_bytes_sent;
2704 info.header_and_padding_bytes_sent +=
2705 infos[i].header_and_padding_bytes_sent;
2706 info.packets_sent += infos[i].packets_sent;
2707 info.total_packet_send_delay_ms += infos[i].total_packet_send_delay_ms;
2708 info.retransmitted_bytes_sent += infos[i].retransmitted_bytes_sent;
2709 info.retransmitted_packets_sent += infos[i].retransmitted_packets_sent;
2710 info.packets_lost += infos[i].packets_lost;
2711 if (infos[i].send_frame_width > info.send_frame_width)
2712 info.send_frame_width = infos[i].send_frame_width;
2713 if (infos[i].send_frame_height > info.send_frame_height)
2714 info.send_frame_height = infos[i].send_frame_height;
2715 info.firs_rcvd += infos[i].firs_rcvd;
2716 info.nacks_rcvd += infos[i].nacks_rcvd;
2717 info.plis_rcvd += infos[i].plis_rcvd;
2718 if (infos[i].report_block_datas.size())
2719 info.report_block_datas.push_back(infos[i].report_block_datas[0]);
2720 if (infos[i].qp_sum) {
2721 if (!info.qp_sum) {
2722 info.qp_sum = 0;
2723 }
2724 info.qp_sum = *info.qp_sum + *infos[i].qp_sum;
2725 }
2726 info.frames_encoded += infos[i].frames_encoded;
2727 info.frames_sent += infos[i].frames_sent;
2728 info.total_encode_time_ms += infos[i].total_encode_time_ms;
2729 info.total_encoded_bytes_target += infos[i].total_encoded_bytes_target;
2730 }
2731 return info;
2732}

2734void WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::FillBitrateInfo(
2735 BandwidthEstimationInfo* bwe_info) {
2736 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
2737 if (stream_ == NULL) {
2738 return;
2739 }
2740 webrtc::VideoSendStream::Stats stats = stream_->GetStats();
2741 for (std::map<uint32_t, webrtc::VideoSendStream::StreamStats>::iterator it =
2742 stats.substreams.begin();
2743 it != stats.substreams.end(); ++it) {
2744 bwe_info->transmit_bitrate += it->second.total_bitrate_bps;
2745 bwe_info->retransmit_bitrate += it->second.retransmit_bitrate_bps;
2746 }
2747 bwe_info->target_enc_bitrate += stats.target_media_bitrate_bps;
2748 bwe_info->actual_enc_bitrate += stats.media_bitrate_bps;
2749}

2768
2769void WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoSendStream::RecreateWebRtcStream() {
2770 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
2771 if (stream_ != NULL) {
2772 call_->DestroyVideoSendStream(stream_);
2773 }
2774
2775 RTC_CHECK(parameters_.codec_settings);
2776 RTC_DCHECK_EQ((parameters_.encoder_config.content_type ==
2777 webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kScreen),
2778 parameters_.options.is_screencast.value_or(false))
2779 << "encoder content type inconsistent with screencast option";
2780 parameters_.encoder_config.encoder_specific_settings =
2781 ConfigureVideoEncoderSettings(parameters_.codec_settings->codec);
2782
2783 webrtc::VideoSendStream::Config config = parameters_.config.Copy();
2784 if (!config.rtp.rtx.ssrcs.empty() && config.rtp.rtx.payload_type == -1) {
2785 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "RTX SSRCs configured but there's no configured RTX "
2786 "payload type the set codec. Ignoring RTX.";
2787 config.rtp.rtx.ssrcs.clear();
2788 }
2789 if (parameters_.encoder_config.number_of_streams == 1) {
2790 // SVC is used instead of simulcast. Remove unnecessary SSRCs.
2791 if (config.rtp.ssrcs.size() > 1) {
2792 config.rtp.ssrcs.resize(1);
2793 if (config.rtp.rtx.ssrcs.size() > 1) {
2794 config.rtp.rtx.ssrcs.resize(1);
2795 }
2796 }
2797 }
2798 stream_ = call_->CreateVideoSendStream(std::move(config),
2799 parameters_.encoder_config.Copy());
2800
2801 parameters_.encoder_config.encoder_specific_settings = NULL;
2802
2803 if (source_) {
2804 stream_->SetSource(source_, GetDegradationPreference());
2805 }
2806
2807 // Call stream_->Start() if necessary conditions are met.
2808 UpdateSendState();
2809}

2872
2873void WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoReceiveStream::ConfigureCodecs(
2874 const std::vector<VideoCodecSettings>& recv_codecs) {
2875 RTC_DCHECK(!recv_codecs.empty());
2876 config_.decoders.clear();
2877 config_.rtp.rtx_associated_payload_types.clear();
2878 config_.rtp.raw_payload_types.clear();
2879 config_.decoder_factory = decoder_factory_;
2880 for (const auto& recv_codec : recv_codecs) {
2881 webrtc::SdpVideoFormat video_format(recv_codec.codec.name,
2882 recv_codec.codec.params);
2883
2884 webrtc::VideoReceiveStream::Decoder decoder;
2885 decoder.video_format = video_format;
2886 decoder.payload_type = recv_codec.codec.id;
2887 decoder.video_format =
2888 webrtc::SdpVideoFormat(recv_codec.codec.name, recv_codec.codec.params);
2889 config_.decoders.push_back(decoder);
2890 config_.rtp.rtx_associated_payload_types[recv_codec.rtx_payload_type] =
2891 recv_codec.codec.id;
2892 if (recv_codec.codec.packetization == kPacketizationParamRaw) {
2893 config_.rtp.raw_payload_types.insert(recv_codec.codec.id);
2894 }
2895 }
2896
2897 const auto& codec = recv_codecs.front();
2898 config_.rtp.ulpfec_payload_type = codec.ulpfec.ulpfec_payload_type;
2899 config_.rtp.red_payload_type = codec.ulpfec.red_payload_type;
2900
2901 config_.rtp.lntf.enabled = HasLntf(codec.codec);
2902 config_.rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms = HasNack(codec.codec) ? kNackHistoryMs : 0;
2903 // The rtx-time parameter can be used to override the hardcoded default for
2904 // the NACK buffer length.
2905 if (codec.rtx_time != -1 && config_.rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms != 0) {
2906 config_.rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms = codec.rtx_time;
2907 }
2908 config_.rtp.rtcp_xr.receiver_reference_time_report = HasRrtr(codec.codec);
2909 if (codec.ulpfec.red_rtx_payload_type != -1) {
2910 config_.rtp
2911 .rtx_associated_payload_types[codec.ulpfec.red_rtx_payload_type] =
2912 codec.ulpfec.red_payload_type;
2913 }
2914}

2996void WebRtcVideoChannel::WebRtcVideoReceiveStream::RecreateWebRtcVideoStream() {
2997 absl::optional<int> base_minimum_playout_delay_ms;
2998 absl::optional<webrtc::VideoReceiveStream::RecordingState> recording_state;
2999 if (stream_) {
3000 base_minimum_playout_delay_ms = stream_->GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs();
3001 recording_state = stream_->SetAndGetRecordingState(
3002 webrtc::VideoReceiveStream::RecordingState(),
3003 /*generate_key_frame=*/false);
3004 call_->DestroyVideoReceiveStream(stream_);

3007

3009 call_->DestroyFlexfecReceiveStream(flexfec_stream_);

3019 config.rtp.packet_sink_ = flexfec_stream_;

3021 if (base_minimum_playout_delay_ms) {
3022 stream_->SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(
3023 base_minimum_playout_delay_ms.value());
3024 }
3025 if (recording_state) {

3027 /*generate_key_frame=*/false);

3244
3245std::vector<WebRtcVideoChannel::VideoCodecSettings>
3246WebRtcVideoChannel::MapCodecs(const std::vector<VideoCodec>& codecs) {
3247 if (codecs.empty()) {
3248 return {};
3249 }
3250
3251 std::vector<VideoCodecSettings> video_codecs;
3252 std::map<int, VideoCodec::CodecType> payload_codec_type;
3253 // |rtx_mapping| maps video payload type to rtx payload type.
3254 std::map<int, int> rtx_mapping;
3255 std::map<int, int> rtx_time_mapping;
3256
3257 webrtc::UlpfecConfig ulpfec_config;
3258 absl::optional<int> flexfec_payload_type;
3259
3260 for (const VideoCodec& in_codec : codecs) {
3261 const int payload_type = in_codec.id;
3262
3263 if (payload_codec_type.find(payload_type) != payload_codec_type.end()) {
3264 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Payload type already registered: "
3265 << in_codec.ToString();
3266 return {};
3267 }
3268 payload_codec_type[payload_type] = in_codec.GetCodecType();
3269
3270 switch (in_codec.GetCodecType()) {
3271 case VideoCodec::CODEC_RED: {
3272 if (ulpfec_config.red_payload_type != -1) {
3273 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
3274 << "Duplicate RED codec: ignoring PT=" << payload_type
3275 << " in favor of PT=" << ulpfec_config.red_payload_type
3276 << " which was specified first.";
3277 break;
3278 }
3279 ulpfec_config.red_payload_type = payload_type;
3280 break;
3281 }
3282
3283 case VideoCodec::CODEC_ULPFEC: {
3284 if (ulpfec_config.ulpfec_payload_type != -1) {
3285 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
3286 << "Duplicate ULPFEC codec: ignoring PT=" << payload_type
3287 << " in favor of PT=" << ulpfec_config.ulpfec_payload_type
3288 << " which was specified first.";
3289 break;
3290 }
3291 ulpfec_config.ulpfec_payload_type = payload_type;
3292 break;
3293 }
3294
3295 case VideoCodec::CODEC_FLEXFEC: {
3296 if (flexfec_payload_type) {
3297 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
3298 << "Duplicate FLEXFEC codec: ignoring PT=" << payload_type
3299 << " in favor of PT=" << *flexfec_payload_type
3300 << " which was specified first.";
3301 break;
3302 }
3303 flexfec_payload_type = payload_type;
3304 break;
3305 }
3306
3307 case VideoCodec::CODEC_RTX: {
3308 int associated_payload_type;
3309 if (!in_codec.GetParam(kCodecParamAssociatedPayloadType,
3310 &associated_payload_type) ||
3311 !IsValidRtpPayloadType(associated_payload_type)) {
3312 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
3313 << "RTX codec with invalid or no associated payload type: "
3314 << in_codec.ToString();
3315 return {};
3316 }
3317 int rtx_time;
3318 if (in_codec.GetParam(kCodecParamRtxTime, &rtx_time) && rtx_time > 0) {
3319 rtx_time_mapping[associated_payload_type] = rtx_time;
3320 }
3321 rtx_mapping[associated_payload_type] = payload_type;
3322 break;
3323 }
3324
3325 case VideoCodec::CODEC_VIDEO: {
3326 video_codecs.emplace_back();
3327 video_codecs.back().codec = in_codec;
3328 break;
3329 }
3330 }
3331 }
3332
3333 // One of these codecs should have been a video codec. Only having FEC
3334 // parameters into this code is a logic error.
3335 RTC_DCHECK(!video_codecs.empty());
3336
3337 for (const auto& entry : rtx_mapping) {
3338 const int associated_payload_type = entry.first;
3339 const int rtx_payload_type = entry.second;
3340 auto it = payload_codec_type.find(associated_payload_type);
3341 if (it == payload_codec_type.end()) {
3342 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "RTX codec (PT=" << rtx_payload_type
3343 << ") mapped to PT=" << associated_payload_type
3344 << " which is not in the codec list.";
3345 return {};
3346 }
3347 const VideoCodec::CodecType associated_codec_type = it->second;
3348 if (associated_codec_type != VideoCodec::CODEC_VIDEO &&
3349 associated_codec_type != VideoCodec::CODEC_RED) {
3350 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
3351 << "RTX PT=" << rtx_payload_type
3352 << " not mapped to regular video codec or RED codec (PT="
3353 << associated_payload_type << ").";
3354 return {};
3355 }
3356
3357 if (associated_payload_type == ulpfec_config.red_payload_type) {
3358 ulpfec_config.red_rtx_payload_type = rtx_payload_type;
3359 }
3360 }
3361
3362 for (VideoCodecSettings& codec_settings : video_codecs) {
3363 const int payload_type = codec_settings.codec.id;
3364 codec_settings.ulpfec = ulpfec_config;
3365 codec_settings.flexfec_payload_type = flexfec_payload_type.value_or(-1);
3366 auto it = rtx_mapping.find(payload_type);
3367 if (it != rtx_mapping.end()) {
3368 const int rtx_payload_type = it->second;
3369 codec_settings.rtx_payload_type = rtx_payload_type;
3370
3371 auto rtx_time_it = rtx_time_mapping.find(payload_type);
3372 if (rtx_time_it != rtx_time_mapping.end()) {
3373 const int rtx_time = rtx_time_it->second;
3374 if (rtx_time < kNackHistoryMs) {
3375 codec_settings.rtx_time = rtx_time;
3376 } else {
3377 codec_settings.rtx_time = kNackHistoryMs;
3378 }
3379 }
3380 }
3381 }
3382
3383 return video_codecs;
3384}

3460void WebRtcVideoChannel::SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
3461 uint32_t ssrc,
3462 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) {
3463 RTC_DCHECK(frame_transformer);
3464 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&thread_checker_);
3465 if (ssrc == 0) {
3466 // If the receiver is unsignaled, save the frame transformer and set it when
3467 // the stream is associated with an ssrc.
3468 unsignaled_frame_transformer_ = std::move(frame_transformer);
3469 return;
3470 }
3471
3472 auto matching_stream = receive_streams_.find(ssrc);
3473 if (matching_stream != receive_streams_.end()) {
3474 matching_stream->second->SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
3475 std::move(frame_transformer));
3476 }
3477}

3495std::vector<webrtc::VideoStream> EncoderStreamFactory::CreateEncoderStreams(
3496 int width,
3497 int height,
3498 const webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig& encoder_config) {
3499 RTC_DCHECK_GT(encoder_config.number_of_streams, 0);
3500 RTC_DCHECK_GE(encoder_config.simulcast_layers.size(),
3501 encoder_config.number_of_streams);
3502
3503 const absl::optional<webrtc::DataRate> experimental_min_bitrate =
3504 GetExperimentalMinVideoBitrate(encoder_config.codec_type);
3505
3506 if (encoder_config.number_of_streams > 1 ||
3507 ((absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec_name_, kVp8CodecName) ||
3508 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec_name_, kH264CodecName)) &&
3509 is_screenshare_ && conference_mode_)) {
3510 return CreateSimulcastOrConferenceModeScreenshareStreams(
3511 width, height, encoder_config, experimental_min_bitrate);
3512 }
3513
3514 return CreateDefaultVideoStreams(width, height, encoder_config,
3515 experimental_min_bitrate);
3516}
3517
3518std::vector<webrtc::VideoStream>
3519EncoderStreamFactory::CreateDefaultVideoStreams(
3520 int width,
3521 int height,
3522 const webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig& encoder_config,
3523 const absl::optional<webrtc::DataRate>& experimental_min_bitrate) const {
3524 std::vector<webrtc::VideoStream> layers;
3525
3526 // For unset max bitrates set default bitrate for non-simulcast.
3527 int max_bitrate_bps =
3528 (encoder_config.max_bitrate_bps > 0)
3529 ? encoder_config.max_bitrate_bps
3530 : GetMaxDefaultVideoBitrateKbps(width, height, is_screenshare_) *
3531 1000;
3532
3533 int min_bitrate_bps =
3534 experimental_min_bitrate
3535 ? rtc::saturated_cast<int>(experimental_min_bitrate->bps())
3536 : webrtc::kDefaultMinVideoBitrateBps;
3537 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].min_bitrate_bps > 0) {
3538 // Use set min bitrate.
3539 min_bitrate_bps = encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].min_bitrate_bps;
3540 // If only min bitrate is configured, make sure max is above min.
3541 if (encoder_config.max_bitrate_bps <= 0)
3542 max_bitrate_bps = std::max(min_bitrate_bps, max_bitrate_bps);
3543 }
3544 int max_framerate = (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].max_framerate > 0)
3545 ? encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].max_framerate
3546 : kDefaultVideoMaxFramerate;
3547
3548 webrtc::VideoStream layer;
3549 layer.width = width;
3550 layer.height = height;
3551 layer.max_framerate = max_framerate;
3552
3553 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].scale_resolution_down_by > 1.) {
3554 layer.width = std::max<size_t>(
3555 layer.width /
3556 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].scale_resolution_down_by,
3557 kMinLayerSize);
3558 layer.height = std::max<size_t>(
3559 layer.height /
3560 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].scale_resolution_down_by,
3561 kMinLayerSize);
3562 }
3563
3564 // In the case that the application sets a max bitrate that's lower than the
3565 // min bitrate, we adjust it down (see bugs.webrtc.org/9141).
3566 layer.min_bitrate_bps = std::min(min_bitrate_bps, max_bitrate_bps);
3567 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].target_bitrate_bps <= 0) {
3568 layer.target_bitrate_bps = max_bitrate_bps;
3569 } else {
3570 layer.target_bitrate_bps =
3571 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].target_bitrate_bps;
3572 }
3573 layer.max_bitrate_bps = max_bitrate_bps;
3574 layer.max_qp = max_qp_;
3575 layer.bitrate_priority = encoder_config.bitrate_priority;
3576
3577 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec_name_, kVp9CodecName)) {
3578 RTC_DCHECK(encoder_config.encoder_specific_settings);
3579 // Use VP9 SVC layering from codec settings which might be initialized
3580 // though field trial in ConfigureVideoEncoderSettings.
3581 webrtc::VideoCodecVP9 vp9_settings;
3582 encoder_config.encoder_specific_settings->FillVideoCodecVp9(&vp9_settings);
3583 layer.num_temporal_layers = vp9_settings.numberOfTemporalLayers;
3584 }
3585
3586 if (IsTemporalLayersSupported(codec_name_)) {
3587 // Use configured number of temporal layers if set.
3588 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].num_temporal_layers) {
3589 layer.num_temporal_layers =
3590 *encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].num_temporal_layers;
3591 }
3592 }
3593 layer.scalability_mode = encoder_config.simulcast_layers[0].scalability_mode;
3594 layers.push_back(layer);
3595 return layers;
3596}
3597
3598std::vector<webrtc::VideoStream>
3599EncoderStreamFactory::CreateSimulcastOrConferenceModeScreenshareStreams(
3600 int width,
3601 int height,
3602 const webrtc::VideoEncoderConfig& encoder_config,
3603 const absl::optional<webrtc::DataRate>& experimental_min_bitrate) const {
3604 std::vector<webrtc::VideoStream> layers;
3605
3606 const bool temporal_layers_supported =
3607 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec_name_, kVp8CodecName) ||
3608 absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec_name_, kH264CodecName);
3609 // Use legacy simulcast screenshare if conference mode is explicitly enabled
3610 // or use the regular simulcast configuration path which is generic.
3611 layers = GetSimulcastConfig(FindRequiredActiveLayers(encoder_config),
3612 encoder_config.number_of_streams, width, height,
3613 encoder_config.bitrate_priority, max_qp_,
3614 is_screenshare_ && conference_mode_,
3615 temporal_layers_supported, trials_);
3616 // Allow an experiment to override the minimum bitrate for the lowest
3617 // spatial layer. The experiment's configuration has the lowest priority.
3618 if (experimental_min_bitrate) {
3619 layers[0].min_bitrate_bps =
3620 rtc::saturated_cast<int>(experimental_min_bitrate->bps());
3621 }
3622 // Update the active simulcast layers and configured bitrates.
3623 bool is_highest_layer_max_bitrate_configured = false;
3624 const bool has_scale_resolution_down_by = absl::c_any_of(
3625 encoder_config.simulcast_layers, [](const webrtc::VideoStream& layer) {
3626 return layer.scale_resolution_down_by != -1.;
3627 });
3628
3629 bool default_scale_factors_used = true;
3630 if (has_scale_resolution_down_by) {
3631 default_scale_factors_used = IsScaleFactorsPowerOfTwo(encoder_config);
3632 }
3633 const bool norm_size_configured =
3634 webrtc::NormalizeSimulcastSizeExperiment::GetBase2Exponent().has_value();
3635 const int normalized_width =
3636 (default_scale_factors_used || norm_size_configured)
3637 ? NormalizeSimulcastSize(width, encoder_config.number_of_streams)
3638 : width;
3639 const int normalized_height =
3640 (default_scale_factors_used || norm_size_configured)
3641 ? NormalizeSimulcastSize(height, encoder_config.number_of_streams)
3642 : height;
3643
3644 for (size_t i = 0; i < layers.size(); ++i) {
3645 layers[i].active = encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].active;
3646 // Update with configured num temporal layers if supported by codec.
3647 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].num_temporal_layers &&
3648 IsTemporalLayersSupported(codec_name_)) {
3649 layers[i].num_temporal_layers =
3650 *encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].num_temporal_layers;
3651 }
3652 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_framerate > 0) {
3653 layers[i].max_framerate =
3654 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_framerate;
3655 }
3656 if (has_scale_resolution_down_by) {
3657 const double scale_resolution_down_by = std::max(
3658 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].scale_resolution_down_by, 1.0);
3659 layers[i].width = std::max(
3660 static_cast<int>(normalized_width / scale_resolution_down_by),
3661 kMinLayerSize);
3662 layers[i].height = std::max(
3663 static_cast<int>(normalized_height / scale_resolution_down_by),
3664 kMinLayerSize);
3665 }
3666 // Update simulcast bitrates with configured min and max bitrate.
3667 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].min_bitrate_bps > 0) {
3668 layers[i].min_bitrate_bps =
3669 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].min_bitrate_bps;
3670 }
3671 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_bitrate_bps > 0) {
3672 layers[i].max_bitrate_bps =
3673 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_bitrate_bps;
3674 }
3675 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].target_bitrate_bps > 0) {
3676 layers[i].target_bitrate_bps =
3677 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].target_bitrate_bps;
3678 }
3679 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].min_bitrate_bps > 0 &&
3680 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_bitrate_bps > 0) {
3681 // Min and max bitrate are configured.
3682 // Set target to 3/4 of the max bitrate (or to max if below min).
3683 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].target_bitrate_bps <= 0)
3684 layers[i].target_bitrate_bps = layers[i].max_bitrate_bps * 3 / 4;
3685 if (layers[i].target_bitrate_bps < layers[i].min_bitrate_bps)
3686 layers[i].target_bitrate_bps = layers[i].max_bitrate_bps;
3687 } else if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].min_bitrate_bps > 0) {
3688 // Only min bitrate is configured, make sure target/max are above min.
3689 layers[i].target_bitrate_bps =
3690 std::max(layers[i].target_bitrate_bps, layers[i].min_bitrate_bps);
3691 layers[i].max_bitrate_bps =
3692 std::max(layers[i].max_bitrate_bps, layers[i].min_bitrate_bps);
3693 } else if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_bitrate_bps > 0) {
3694 // Only max bitrate is configured, make sure min/target are below max.
3695 // Keep target bitrate if it is set explicitly in encoding config.
3696 // Otherwise set target bitrate to 3/4 of the max bitrate
3697 // or the one calculated from GetSimulcastConfig() which is larger.
3698 layers[i].min_bitrate_bps =
3699 std::min(layers[i].min_bitrate_bps, layers[i].max_bitrate_bps);
3700 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].target_bitrate_bps <= 0) {
3701 layers[i].target_bitrate_bps = std::max(
3702 layers[i].target_bitrate_bps, layers[i].max_bitrate_bps * 3 / 4);
3703 }
3704 layers[i].target_bitrate_bps = std::max(
3705 std::min(layers[i].target_bitrate_bps, layers[i].max_bitrate_bps),
3706 layers[i].min_bitrate_bps);
3707 }
3708 if (i == layers.size() - 1) {
3709 is_highest_layer_max_bitrate_configured =
3710 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].max_bitrate_bps > 0;
3711 }
3712 }
3713 if (!is_screenshare_ && !is_highest_layer_max_bitrate_configured &&
3714 encoder_config.max_bitrate_bps > 0) {
3715 // No application-configured maximum for the largest layer.
3716 // If there is bitrate leftover, give it to the largest layer.
3717 BoostMaxSimulcastLayer(
3718 webrtc::DataRate::BitsPerSec(encoder_config.max_bitrate_bps), &layers);
3719 }
3720
3721 // Sort the layers by max_bitrate_bps, they might not always be from
3722 // smallest to biggest
3723 std::vector<size_t> index(layers.size());
3724 std::iota(index.begin(), index.end(), 0);
3725 std::stable_sort(index.begin(), index.end(), [&layers](size_t a, size_t b) {
3726 return layers[a].max_bitrate_bps < layers[b].max_bitrate_bps;
3727 });
3728
3729 if (!layers[index[0]].active) {
3730 // Adjust min bitrate of the first active layer to allow it to go as low as
3731 // the lowest (now inactive) layer could.
3732 // Otherwise, if e.g. a single HD stream is active, it would have 600kbps
3733 // min bitrate, which would always be allocated to the stream.
3734 // This would lead to congested network, dropped frames and overall bad
3735 // experience.
3736
3737 const int min_configured_bitrate = layers[index[0]].min_bitrate_bps;
3738 for (size_t i = 0; i < layers.size(); ++i) {
3739 if (layers[index[i]].active) {
3740 layers[index[i]].min_bitrate_bps = min_configured_bitrate;
3741 break;
3742 }
3743 }
3744 }
3745
3746 return layers;
3747}
